77 // Hot/cold operator new takes an 8 bit hotness hint, where 0 is the coldest ----
78 // and 255 is the hottest. Default to 1 value away from the coldest and hottest ----
79 // hints, so that the compiler hinted allocations are slightly less strong than ----
80 // manually inserted hints at the two extremes. ----
81 static cl::opt ColdNewHintValue( ----
82 "cold-new-hint-value", cl::Hidden, cl::init(1), ----
83 cl::desc("Value to pass to hot/cold operator new for cold allocation")); ----
84 static cl::opt HotNewHintValue( ----
85 "hot-new-hint-value", cl::Hidden, cl::init(254), ----
86 cl::desc("Value to pass to hot/cold operator new for hot allocation")); ----

92 static bool ignoreCallingConv(LibFunc Func) { 0

94 Func == LibFunc_llabs || Func == LibFunc_strlen; 0

97 /// Return true if it is only used in equality comparisons with With. ----
98 static bool isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(Value *V, Value *With) { 0
99 for (User *U : V->users()) { 0
100 if (ICmpInst *IC = dyn_cast(U)) 0
101 if (IC->isEquality() && IC->getOperand(1) == With) 0
102 continue; 0
103 // Unknown instruction. ----
104 return false; 0
105 } ----
106 return true; 0
107 } ----

121 // Convert the entire string Str representing an integer in Base, up to ----
122 // the terminating nul if present, to a constant according to the rules ----
123 // of strtoul[l] or, when AsSigned is set, of strtol[l]. On success ----
124 // return the result, otherwise null. ----
125 // The function assumes the string is encoded in ASCII and carefully ----
126 // avoids converting sequences (including "") that the corresponding ----
127 // library call might fail and set errno for. ----
128 static Value *convertStrToInt(CallInst *CI, StringRef &Str, Value *EndPtr, 0
129 uint64_t Base, bool AsSigned, IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
130 if (Base < 2 || Base > 36) 0
131 if (Base != 0) 0
132 // Fail for an invalid base (required by POSIX). ----
133 return nullptr; 0
134 ----
135 // Current offset into the original string to reflect in EndPtr. ----
136 size_t Offset = 0; 0
137 // Strip leading whitespace. ----
138 for ( ; Offset != Str.size(); ++Offset) 0
139 if (!isSpace((unsigned char)Str[Offset])) { 0
140 Str = Str.substr(Offset); 0
141 break; 0
142 } ----
143 ----
144 if (Str.empty()) 0
145 // Fail for empty subject sequences (POSIX allows but doesn't require ----
146 // strtol[l]/strtoul[l] to fail with EINVAL). ----
147 return nullptr; 0
148 ----
149 // Strip but remember the sign. ----
150 bool Negate = Str[0] == '-'; 0
151 if (Str[0] == '-' || Str[0] == '+') { 0
152 Str = Str.drop_front(); 0
153 if (Str.empty()) 0
154 // Fail for a sign with nothing after it. ----
155 return nullptr; 0
156 ++Offset; 0
157 } ----
158 ----
159 // Set Max to the absolute value of the minimum (for signed), or ----
160 // to the maximum (for unsigned) value representable in the type. ----
161 Type *RetTy = CI->getType(); 0
162 unsigned NBits = RetTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(); 0
163 uint64_t Max = AsSigned && Negate ? 1 : 0; 0
164 Max += AsSigned ? maxIntN(NBits) : maxUIntN(NBits); 0
165 ----
166 // Autodetect Base if it's zero and consume the "0x" prefix. ----
167 if (Str.size() > 1) { 0
168 if (Str[0] == '0') { 0
169 if (toUpper((unsigned char)Str[1]) == 'X') { 0
170 if (Str.size() == 2 || (Base && Base != 16)) 0
171 // Fail if Base doesn't allow the "0x" prefix or for the prefix ----
172 // alone that implementations like BSD set errno to EINVAL for. ----
173 return nullptr; 0
174 ----
175 Str = Str.drop_front(2); 0
176 Offset += 2; 0
177 Base = 16; 0
178 } ----
179 else if (Base == 0) 0
180 Base = 8; 0
181 } else if (Base == 0) 0
182 Base = 10; 0
183 } ----
184 else if (Base == 0) 0
185 Base = 10; 0
186 ----
187 // Convert the rest of the subject sequence, not including the sign, ----
188 // to its uint64_t representation (this assumes the source character ----
189 // set is ASCII). ----
190 uint64_t Result = 0; 0
191 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Str.size(); ++i) { 0
192 unsigned char DigVal = Str[i]; 0
193 if (isDigit(DigVal)) 0
194 DigVal = DigVal - '0'; 0
195 else { ----
196 DigVal = toUpper(DigVal); 0
197 if (isAlpha(DigVal)) 0
198 DigVal = DigVal - 'A' + 10; 0
199 else ----
200 return nullptr; 0
201 } ----
202 ----
203 if (DigVal >= Base) 0
204 // Fail if the digit is not valid in the Base. ----
205 return nullptr; 0
206 ----
207 // Add the digit and fail if the result is not representable in ----
208 // the (unsigned form of the) destination type. ----
209 bool VFlow; ----
210 Result = SaturatingMultiplyAdd(Result, Base, (uint64_t)DigVal, &VFlow); 0
211 if (VFlow || Result > Max) 0
212 return nullptr; 0
213 } ----
214 ----
215 if (EndPtr) { 0
216 // Store the pointer to the end. ----
217 Value *Off = B.getInt64(Offset + Str.size()); 0
218 Value *StrBeg = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
219 Value *StrEnd = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), StrBeg, Off, "endptr"); 0
220 B.CreateStore(StrEnd, EndPtr); 0
221 } ----
222 ----
223 if (Negate) 0
224 // Unsigned negation doesn't overflow. ----
225 Result = -Result; 0
226 ----
227 return ConstantInt::get(RetTy, Result); 0
228 } ----

230 static bool canTransformToMemCmp(CallInst *CI, Value *Str, uint64_t Len, 0
231 const DataLayout &DL) { ----
232 if (!isOnlyUsedInZeroComparison(CI)) 0
233 return false; 0
234 ----
235 if (!isDereferenceableAndAlignedPointer(Str, Align(1), APInt(64, Len), DL)) 0
236 return false; 0
237 ----
238 if (CI->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeMemory)) 0
239 return false; 0
240 ----
241 return true; 0
242 } ----

244 static void annotateDereferenceableBytes(CallInst *CI, 0
245 ArrayRef ArgNos, ----
246 uint64_t DereferenceableBytes) { ----
247 const Function *F = CI->getCaller(); 0
248 if (!F) 0
249 return; 0
250 for (unsigned ArgNo : ArgNos) { 0
251 uint64_t DerefBytes = DereferenceableBytes; 0
252 unsigned AS = CI->getArgOperand(ArgNo)->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
253 if (!llvm::NullPointerIsDefined(F, AS) || 0
254 CI->paramHasAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NonNull)) 0
255 DerefBytes = std::max(CI->getParamDereferenceableOrNullBytes(ArgNo), 0
256 DereferenceableBytes); ----
257 ----
258 if (CI->getParamDereferenceableBytes(ArgNo) < DerefBytes) { 0
259 CI->removeParamAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::Dereferenceable); 0
260 if (!llvm::NullPointerIsDefined(F, AS) || 0
261 CI->paramHasAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NonNull)) 0
262 CI->removeParamAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull); 0
263 CI->addParamAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::getWithDereferenceableBytes( 0
264 CI->getContext(), DerefBytes)); ----
265 } ----
266 } ----
267 } ----

269 static void annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CallInst *CI, 0
270 ArrayRef ArgNos) { ----
271 Function *F = CI->getCaller(); 0
272 if (!F) 0
273 return; 0
274 ----
275 for (unsigned ArgNo : ArgNos) { 0
276 if (!CI->paramHasAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NoUndef)) 0
277 CI->addParamAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NoUndef); 0
278 ----
279 if (!CI->paramHasAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NonNull)) { 0
280 unsigned AS = ----
281 CI->getArgOperand(ArgNo)->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
282 if (llvm::NullPointerIsDefined(F, AS)) 0
283 continue; 0
284 CI->addParamAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NonNull); 0
285 } ----
286 ----
287 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, ArgNo, 1); 0
288 } ----
289 } ----

291 static void annotateNonNullAndDereferenceable(CallInst *CI, ArrayRef ArgNos, 0
292 Value *Size, const DataLayout &DL) { ----
293 if (ConstantInt *LenC = dyn_cast(Size)) { 0
294 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, ArgNos); 0
295 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, ArgNos, LenC->getZExtValue()); 0
296 } else if (isKnownNonZero(Size, DL)) { 0
297 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, ArgNos); 0
298 const APInt *X, *Y; ----
299 uint64_t DerefMin = 1; 0
300 if (match(Size, m_Select(m_Value(), m_APInt(X), m_APInt(Y)))) { 0
301 DerefMin = std::min(X->getZExtValue(), Y->getZExtValue()); 0
302 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, ArgNos, DerefMin); 0
303 } ----
304 } ----
305 } 0

307 // Copy CallInst "flags" like musttail, notail, and tail. Return New param for ----
308 // easier chaining. Calls to emit* and B.createCall should probably be wrapped ----
309 // in this function when New is created to replace Old. Callers should take ----
310 // care to check Old.isMustTailCall() if they aren't replacing Old directly ----
311 // with New. ----
312 static Value *copyFlags(const CallInst &Old, Value *New) { 0
313 assert(!Old.isMustTailCall() && "do not copy musttail call flags"); 0
314 assert(!Old.isNoTailCall() && "do not copy notail call flags"); 0
315 if (auto *NewCI = dyn_cast_or_null(New)) 0
316 NewCI->setTailCallKind(Old.getTailCallKind()); 0
317 return New; 0
318 } ----

321 NewCI->setAttributes(AttributeList::get( 0
322 NewCI->getContext(), {NewCI->getAttributes(), Old.getAttributes()})); 0
323 NewCI->removeRetAttrs(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(NewCI->getType())); 0
324 return copyFlags(Old, NewCI); 0
325 } ----

329 return Len >= Str.size() ? Str : Str.substr(0, Len); 0

336 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCat(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
337 // Extract some information from the instruction ----
338 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
339 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
340 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, {0, 1}); 0
341 ----
342 // See if we can get the length of the input string. ----
343 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src); 0
344 if (Len) 0
345 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, Len); 0
346 else ----
347 return nullptr; 0
348 --Len; // Unbias length. 0
349 ----
350 // Handle the simple, do-nothing case: strcat(x, "") -> x ----
351 if (Len == 0) 0
352 return Dst; 0
353 ----
354 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrLenMemCpy(Src, Dst, Len, B)); 0
355 } ----
356 ----
357 Value *LibCallSimplifier::emitStrLenMemCpy(Value *Src, Value *Dst, uint64_t Len, 0
358 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
359 // We need to find the end of the destination string. That's where the ----
360 // memory is to be moved to. We just generate a call to strlen. ----
361 Value *DstLen = emitStrLen(Dst, B, DL, TLI); 0
362 if (!DstLen) 0
363 return nullptr; 0
364 ----
365 // Now that we have the destination's length, we must index into the ----
366 // destination's pointer to get the actual memcpy destination (end of ----
367 // the string .. we're concatenating). ----
368 Value *CpyDst = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, DstLen, "endptr"); 0
369 ----
370 // We have enough information to now generate the memcpy call to do the ----
371 // concatenation for us. Make a memcpy to copy the nul byte with align = 1. ----
372 B.CreateMemCpy( 0
373 CpyDst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), ----
374 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(Src->getContext()), Len + 1)); 0
375 return Dst; 0
376 } ----

378 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNCat(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
379 // Extract some information from the instruction. ----
380 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
381 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
382 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
383 uint64_t Len; ----
384 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
385 if (isKnownNonZero(Size, DL)) 0
386 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 1); 0
387 ----
388 // We don't do anything if length is not constant. ----
389 ConstantInt *LengthArg = dyn_cast(Size); 0
390 if (LengthArg) { 0
391 Len = LengthArg->getZExtValue(); 0
392 // strncat(x, c, 0) -> x ----
393 if (!Len) 0
394 return Dst; 0
395 } else { ----
396 return nullptr; 0
397 } ----
398 ----
399 // See if we can get the length of the input string. ----
400 uint64_t SrcLen = GetStringLength(Src); 0
401 if (SrcLen) { 0
402 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, SrcLen); 0
403 --SrcLen; // Unbias length. 0
404 } else { ----
405 return nullptr; 0
406 } ----
407 ----
408 // strncat(x, "", c) -> x ----
409 if (SrcLen == 0) 0
410 return Dst; 0
411 ----
412 // We don't optimize this case. ----
413 if (Len < SrcLen) 0
414 return nullptr; 0
415 ----
416 // strncat(x, s, c) -> strcat(x, s) ----
417 // s is constant so the strcat can be optimized further. ----
418 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrLenMemCpy(Src, Dst, SrcLen, B)); 0
419 } ----

421 // Helper to transform memchr(S, C, N) == S to N && *S == C and, when ----
422 // NBytes is null, strchr(S, C) to *S == C. A precondition of the function ----
423 // is that either S is dereferenceable or the value of N is nonzero. ----
424 static Value* memChrToCharCompare(CallInst *CI, Value *NBytes, 0
425 IRBuilderBase &B, const DataLayout &DL) ----
426 { ----
427 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
428 Value *CharVal = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
429 ----
430 // Fold memchr(A, C, N) == A to N && *A == C. ----
431 Type *CharTy = B.getInt8Ty(); 0
432 Value *Char0 = B.CreateLoad(CharTy, Src); 0
433 CharVal = B.CreateTrunc(CharVal, CharTy); 0
434 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpEQ(Char0, CharVal, "char0cmp"); 0
435 ----
436 if (NBytes) { 0
437 Value *Zero = ConstantInt::get(NBytes->getType(), 0); 0
438 Value *And = B.CreateICmpNE(NBytes, Zero); 0
439 Cmp = B.CreateLogicalAnd(And, Cmp); 0
440 } ----
441 ----
442 Value *NullPtr = Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
443 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, Src, NullPtr); 0
444 } ----

446 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
447 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
448 Value *CharVal = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
449 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
450 ----
451 if (isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(CI, SrcStr)) 0
452 return memChrToCharCompare(CI, nullptr, B, DL); 0
453 ----
454 // If the second operand is non-constant, see if we can compute the length ----
455 // of the input string and turn this into memchr. ----
456 ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast(CharVal); 0
457 if (!CharC) { 0
458 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(SrcStr); 0
459 if (Len) 0
460 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 0, Len); 0
461 else ----
462 return nullptr; 0
463 ----
464 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
465 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType(); 0
466 unsigned IntBits = TLI->getIntSize(); 0
467 if (!FT->getParamType(1)->isIntegerTy(IntBits)) // memchr needs 'int'. 0
468 return nullptr; 0
469 ----
470 unsigned SizeTBits = TLI->getSizeTSize(*CI->getModule()); 0
471 Type *SizeTTy = IntegerType::get(CI->getContext(), SizeTBits); 0
472 return copyFlags(*CI, 0
473 emitMemChr(SrcStr, CharVal, // include nul. ----
474 ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, Len), B, 0
475 DL, TLI)); 0
476 } ----
477 ----
478 if (CharC->isZero()) { 0
479 Value *NullPtr = Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
480 if (isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(CI, NullPtr)) 0
481 // Pre-empt the transformation to strlen below and fold ----
482 // strchr(A, '\0') == null to false. ----
483 return B.CreateIntToPtr(B.getTrue(), CI->getType()); 0
484 } ----
485 ----
486 // Otherwise, the character is a constant, see if the first argument is ----
487 // a string literal. If so, we can constant fold. ----
488 StringRef Str; 0
489 if (!getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str)) { 0
490 if (CharC->isZero()) // strchr(p, 0) -> p + strlen(p) 0
491 if (Value *StrLen = emitStrLen(SrcStr, B, DL, TLI)) 0
492 return B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, StrLen, "strchr"); 0
493 return nullptr; 0
494 } ----
495 ----
496 // Compute the offset, make sure to handle the case when we're searching for ----
497 // zero (a weird way to spell strlen). ----
498 size_t I = (0xFF & CharC->getSExtValue()) == 0 0
499 ? Str.size() 0
500 : Str.find(CharC->getSExtValue()); 0
501 if (I == StringRef::npos) // Didn't find the char. strchr returns null. 0
502 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
503 ----
504 // strchr(s+n,c) -> gep(s+n+i,c) ----
505 return B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, B.getInt64(I), "strchr"); 0
506 } ----

508 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrRChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
509 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
510 Value *CharVal = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
511 ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast(CharVal); 0
512 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
513 ----
514 StringRef Str; 0
515 if (!getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str)) { 0
516 // strrchr(s, 0) -> strchr(s, 0) ----
517 if (CharC && CharC->isZero()) 0
518 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrChr(SrcStr, '\0', B, TLI)); 0
519 return nullptr; 0
520 } ----
521 ----
522 unsigned SizeTBits = TLI->getSizeTSize(*CI->getModule()); 0
523 Type *SizeTTy = IntegerType::get(CI->getContext(), SizeTBits); 0
524 ----
525 // Try to expand strrchr to the memrchr nonstandard extension if it's ----
526 // available, or simply fail otherwise. ----
527 uint64_t NBytes = Str.size() + 1; // Include the terminating nul. 0
528 Value *Size = ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, NBytes); 0
529 return copyFlags(*CI, emitMemRChr(SrcStr, CharVal, Size, B, DL, TLI)); 0
530 } ----

532 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
533 Value *Str1P = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Str2P = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
534 if (Str1P == Str2P) // strcmp(x,x) -> 0 0
535 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
536 ----
537 StringRef Str1, Str2; 0
538 bool HasStr1 = getConstantStringInfo(Str1P, Str1); 0
539 bool HasStr2 = getConstantStringInfo(Str2P, Str2); 0
540 ----
541 // strcmp(x, y) -> cnst (if both x and y are constant strings) ----
542 if (HasStr1 && HasStr2) 0
543 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0
544 std::clamp(Str1.compare(Str2), -1, 1)); 0
545 ----
546 if (HasStr1 && Str1.empty()) // strcmp("", x) -> -*x 0
547 return B.CreateNeg(B.CreateZExt( 0
548 B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str2P, "strcmpload"), CI->getType())); 0
549 ----
550 if (HasStr2 && Str2.empty()) // strcmp(x,"") -> *x 0
551 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str1P, "strcmpload"), 0
552 CI->getType()); 0
553 ----
554 // strcmp(P, "x") -> memcmp(P, "x", 2) ----
555 uint64_t Len1 = GetStringLength(Str1P); 0
556 if (Len1) 0
557 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 0, Len1); 0
558 uint64_t Len2 = GetStringLength(Str2P); 0
559 if (Len2) 0
560 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, Len2); 0
561 ----
562 if (Len1 && Len2) { 0
563 return copyFlags( 0
564 *CI, emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, ----
565 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), 0
566 std::min(Len1, Len2)), 0
567 B, DL, TLI)); 0
568 } ----
569 ----
570 // strcmp to memcmp ----
571 if (!HasStr1 && HasStr2) { 0
572 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str1P, Len2, DL)) 0
573 return copyFlags( 0
574 *CI, ----
575 emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, ----
576 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len2), 0
577 B, DL, TLI)); 0
578 } else if (HasStr1 && !HasStr2) { 0
579 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str2P, Len1, DL)) 0
580 return copyFlags( 0
581 *CI, ----
582 emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, ----
583 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len1), 0
584 B, DL, TLI)); 0
585 } ----
586 ----
587 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, {0, 1}); 0
588 return nullptr; 0
589 } ----
590 ----
591 // Optimize a memcmp or, when StrNCmp is true, strncmp call CI with constant ----
592 // arrays LHS and RHS and nonconstant Size. ----
593 static Value *optimizeMemCmpVarSize(CallInst *CI, Value *LHS, Value *RHS, ----
594 Value *Size, bool StrNCmp, ----
595 IRBuilderBase &B, const DataLayout &DL); ----
596 ----
597 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
598 Value *Str1P = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
599 Value *Str2P = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
600 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
601 if (Str1P == Str2P) // strncmp(x,x,n) -> 0 0
602 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
603 ----
604 if (isKnownNonZero(Size, DL)) 0
605 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, {0, 1}); 0
606 // Get the length argument if it is constant. ----
607 uint64_t Length; ----
608 if (ConstantInt *LengthArg = dyn_cast(Size)) 0
609 Length = LengthArg->getZExtValue(); 0
610 else ----
611 return optimizeMemCmpVarSize(CI, Str1P, Str2P, Size, true, B, DL); 0
612 ----
613 if (Length == 0) // strncmp(x,y,0) -> 0 0
614 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
615 ----
616 if (Length == 1) // strncmp(x,y,1) -> memcmp(x,y,1) 0
617 return copyFlags(*CI, emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, Size, B, DL, TLI)); 0
618 ----
619 StringRef Str1, Str2; 0
620 bool HasStr1 = getConstantStringInfo(Str1P, Str1); 0
621 bool HasStr2 = getConstantStringInfo(Str2P, Str2); 0
622 ----
623 // strncmp(x, y) -> cnst (if both x and y are constant strings) ----
624 if (HasStr1 && HasStr2) { 0
625 // Avoid truncating the 64-bit Length to 32 bits in ILP32. ----
626 StringRef SubStr1 = substr(Str1, Length); 0
627 StringRef SubStr2 = substr(Str2, Length); 0
628 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0
629 std::clamp(SubStr1.compare(SubStr2), -1, 1)); 0
630 } ----
631 ----
632 if (HasStr1 && Str1.empty()) // strncmp("", x, n) -> -*x 0
633 return B.CreateNeg(B.CreateZExt( 0
634 B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str2P, "strcmpload"), CI->getType())); 0
635 ----
636 if (HasStr2 && Str2.empty()) // strncmp(x, "", n) -> *x 0
637 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str1P, "strcmpload"), 0
638 CI->getType()); 0
639 ----
640 uint64_t Len1 = GetStringLength(Str1P); 0
641 if (Len1) 0
642 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 0, Len1); 0
643 uint64_t Len2 = GetStringLength(Str2P); 0
644 if (Len2) 0
645 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, Len2); 0
646 ----
647 // strncmp to memcmp ----
648 if (!HasStr1 && HasStr2) { 0
649 Len2 = std::min(Len2, Length); 0
650 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str1P, Len2, DL)) 0
651 return copyFlags( 0
652 *CI, ----
653 emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, ----
654 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len2), 0
655 B, DL, TLI)); 0
656 } else if (HasStr1 && !HasStr2) { 0
657 Len1 = std::min(Len1, Length); 0
658 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str2P, Len1, DL)) 0
659 return copyFlags( 0
660 *CI, ----
661 emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, ----
662 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len1), 0
663 B, DL, TLI)); 0
664 } ----
665 ----
666 return nullptr; 0
667 } ----
668 ----
669 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNDup(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
670 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
671 ConstantInt *Size = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(1)); 0
672 uint64_t SrcLen = GetStringLength(Src); 0
673 if (SrcLen && Size) { 0
674 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 0, SrcLen); 0
675 if (SrcLen <= Size->getZExtValue() + 1) 0
676 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrDup(Src, B, TLI)); 0
677 } ----
678 ----
679 return nullptr; 0
680 } ----
681 ----
682 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
683 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
684 if (Dst == Src) // strcpy(x,x) -> x 0
685 return Src; 0
686 ----
687 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, {0, 1}); 0
688 // See if we can get the length of the input string. ----
689 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src); 0
690 if (Len) 0
691 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, Len); 0
692 else ----
693 return nullptr; 0
694 ----
695 // We have enough information to now generate the memcpy call to do the ----
696 // copy for us. Make a memcpy to copy the nul byte with align = 1. ----
697 CallInst *NewCI = ----
698 B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), 0
699 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len)); 0
700 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
701 return Dst; 0
702 } ----
703 ----
704 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStpCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
705 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
706 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
707 ----
708 // stpcpy(d,s) -> strcpy(d,s) if the result is not used. ----
709 if (CI->use_empty()) 0
710 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrCpy(Dst, Src, B, TLI)); 0
711 ----
712 if (Dst == Src) { // stpcpy(x,x) -> x+strlen(x) 0
713 Value *StrLen = emitStrLen(Src, B, DL, TLI); 0
714 return StrLen ? B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, StrLen) : nullptr; 0
715 } ----
716 ----
717 // See if we can get the length of the input string. ----
718 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src); 0
719 if (Len) 0
720 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, Len); 0
721 else ----
722 return nullptr; 0
723 ----
724 Type *PT = Callee->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0); 0
725 Value *LenV = ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), Len); 0
726 Value *DstEnd = B.CreateInBoundsGEP( 0
727 B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), Len - 1)); 0
728 ----
729 // We have enough information to now generate the memcpy call to do the ----
730 // copy for us. Make a memcpy to copy the nul byte with align = 1. ----
731 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), LenV); 0
732 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
733 return DstEnd; 0
734 } ----
735 ----
736 // Optimize a call to size_t strlcpy(char*, const char*, size_t). ----
737 ----
738 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrLCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
739 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
740 if (isKnownNonZero(Size, DL)) 0
741 // Like snprintf, the function stores into the destination only when ----
742 // the size argument is nonzero. ----
743 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
744 // The function reads the source argument regardless of Size (it returns ----
745 // its length). ----
746 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 1); 0
747 ----
748 uint64_t NBytes; ----
749 if (ConstantInt *SizeC = dyn_cast(Size)) 0
750 NBytes = SizeC->getZExtValue(); 0
751 else ----
752 return nullptr; 0
753 ----
754 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
755 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
756 if (NBytes <= 1) { 0
757 if (NBytes == 1) 0
758 // For a call to strlcpy(D, S, 1) first store a nul in *D. ----
759 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), Dst); 0
760 ----
761 // Transform strlcpy(D, S, 0) to a call to strlen(S). ----
762 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrLen(Src, B, DL, TLI)); 0
763 } ----
764 ----
765 // Try to determine the length of the source, substituting its size ----
766 // when it's not nul-terminated (as it's required to be) to avoid ----
767 // reading past its end. ----
768 StringRef Str; 0
769 if (!getConstantStringInfo(Src, Str, /*TrimAtNul=*/false)) 0
770 return nullptr; 0
771 ----
772 uint64_t SrcLen = Str.find('\0'); 0
773 // Set if the terminating nul should be copied by the call to memcpy ----
774 // below. ----
775 bool NulTerm = SrcLen < NBytes; 0
776 ----
777 if (NulTerm) 0
778 // Overwrite NBytes with the number of bytes to copy, including ----
779 // the terminating nul. ----
780 NBytes = SrcLen + 1; 0
781 else { ----
782 // Set the length of the source for the function to return to its ----
783 // size, and cap NBytes at the same. ----
784 SrcLen = std::min(SrcLen, uint64_t(Str.size())); 0
785 NBytes = std::min(NBytes - 1, SrcLen); 0
786 } ----
787 ----
788 if (SrcLen == 0) { 0
789 // Transform strlcpy(D, "", N) to (*D = '\0, 0). ----
790 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), Dst); 0
791 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
792 } ----
793 ----
794 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
795 Type *PT = Callee->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0); 0
796 // Transform strlcpy(D, S, N) to memcpy(D, S, N') where N' is the lower ----
797 // bound on strlen(S) + 1 and N, optionally followed by a nul store to ----
798 // D[N' - 1] if necessary. ----
799 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), 0
800 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), NBytes)); 0
801 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
802 ----
803 if (!NulTerm) { 0
804 Value *EndOff = ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), NBytes); 0
805 Value *EndPtr = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, EndOff); 0
806 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), EndPtr); 0
807 } ----
808 ----
809 // Like snprintf, strlcpy returns the number of nonzero bytes that would ----
810 // have been copied if the bound had been sufficiently big (which in this ----
811 // case is strlen(Src)). ----
812 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), SrcLen); 0
813 } ----
814 ----
815 // Optimize a call CI to either stpncpy when RetEnd is true, or to strncpy ----
816 // otherwise. ----
817 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStringNCpy(CallInst *CI, bool RetEnd, 0
818 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
819 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
820 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
821 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
822 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
823 ----
824 if (isKnownNonZero(Size, DL)) { 0
825 // Both st{p,r}ncpy(D, S, N) access the source and destination arrays ----
826 // only when N is nonzero. ----
827 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
828 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 1); 0
829 } ----
830 ----
831 // If the "bound" argument is known set N to it. Otherwise set it to ----
832 // UINT64_MAX and handle it later. ----
833 uint64_t N = UINT64_MAX; 0
834 if (ConstantInt *SizeC = dyn_cast(Size)) 0
835 N = SizeC->getZExtValue(); 0
836 ----
837 if (N == 0) 0
838 // Fold st{p,r}ncpy(D, S, 0) to D. ----
839 return Dst; 0
840 ----
841 if (N == 1) { 0
842 Type *CharTy = B.getInt8Ty(); 0
843 Value *CharVal = B.CreateLoad(CharTy, Src, "stxncpy.char0"); 0
844 B.CreateStore(CharVal, Dst); 0
845 if (!RetEnd) 0
846 // Transform strncpy(D, S, 1) to return (*D = *S), D. ----
847 return Dst; 0
848 ----
849 // Transform stpncpy(D, S, 1) to return (*D = *S) ? D + 1 : D. ----
850 Value *ZeroChar = ConstantInt::get(CharTy, 0); 0
851 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpEQ(CharVal, ZeroChar, "stpncpy.char0cmp"); 0
852 ----
853 Value *Off1 = B.getInt32(1); 0
854 Value *EndPtr = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(CharTy, Dst, Off1, "stpncpy.end"); 0
855 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, Dst, EndPtr, "stpncpy.sel"); 0
856 } ----
857 ----
858 // If the length of the input string is known set SrcLen to it. ----
859 uint64_t SrcLen = GetStringLength(Src); 0
860 if (SrcLen) 0
861 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, 1, SrcLen); 0
862 else ----
863 return nullptr; 0
864 ----
865 --SrcLen; // Unbias length. 0
866 ----
867 if (SrcLen == 0) { 0
868 // Transform st{p,r}ncpy(D, "", N) to memset(D, '\0', N) for any N. ----
869 Align MemSetAlign = ----
870 CI->getAttributes().getParamAttrs(0).getAlignment().valueOrOne(); 0
871 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemSet(Dst, B.getInt8('\0'), Size, MemSetAlign); 0
872 AttrBuilder ArgAttrs(CI->getContext(), CI->getAttributes().getParamAttrs(0)); 0
873 NewCI->setAttributes(NewCI->getAttributes().addParamAttributes( 0
874 CI->getContext(), 0, ArgAttrs)); ----
875 copyFlags(*CI, NewCI); 0
876 return Dst; 0
877 } 0
878 ----
879 if (N > SrcLen + 1) { 0
880 if (N > 128) 0
881 // Bail if N is large or unknown. ----
882 return nullptr; 0
883 ----
884 // st{p,r}ncpy(D, "a", N) -> memcpy(D, "a\0\0\0", N) for N <= 128. ----
885 StringRef Str; 0
886 if (!getConstantStringInfo(Src, Str)) 0
887 return nullptr; 0
888 std::string SrcStr = Str.str(); 0
889 // Create a bigger, nul-padded array with the same length, SrcLen, ----
890 // as the original string. ----
891 SrcStr.resize(N, '\0'); 0
892 Src = B.CreateGlobalString(SrcStr, "str"); 0
893 } 0
894 ----
895 Type *PT = Callee->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0); 0
896 // st{p,r}ncpy(D, S, N) -> memcpy(align 1 D, align 1 S, N) when both ----
897 // S and N are constant. ----
898 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), 0
899 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), N)); 0
900 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
901 if (!RetEnd) 0
902 return Dst; 0
903 ----
904 // stpncpy(D, S, N) returns the address of the first null in D if it writes ----
905 // one, otherwise D + N. ----
906 Value *Off = B.getInt64(std::min(SrcLen, N)); 0
907 return B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, Off, "endptr"); 0
908 } ----
909 ----
910 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStringLength(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
911 unsigned CharSize, ----
912 Value *Bound) { ----
913 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
914 Type *CharTy = B.getIntNTy(CharSize); 0
915 ----
916 if (isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI) && 0
917 (!Bound || isKnownNonZero(Bound, DL))) { 0
918 // Fold strlen: ----
919 // strlen(x) != 0 --> *x != 0 ----
920 // strlen(x) == 0 --> *x == 0 ----
921 // and likewise strnlen with constant N > 0: ----
922 // strnlen(x, N) != 0 --> *x != 0 ----
923 // strnlen(x, N) == 0 --> *x == 0 ----
924 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(CharTy, Src, "char0"), 0
925 CI->getType()); 0
926 } ----
927 ----
928 if (Bound) { 0
929 if (ConstantInt *BoundCst = dyn_cast(Bound)) { 0
930 if (BoundCst->isZero()) 0
931 // Fold strnlen(s, 0) -> 0 for any s, constant or otherwise. ----
932 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
933 ----
934 if (BoundCst->isOne()) { 0
935 // Fold strnlen(s, 1) -> *s ? 1 : 0 for any s. ----
936 Value *CharVal = B.CreateLoad(CharTy, Src, "strnlen.char0"); 0
937 Value *ZeroChar = ConstantInt::get(CharTy, 0); 0
938 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpNE(CharVal, ZeroChar, "strnlen.char0cmp"); 0
939 return B.CreateZExt(Cmp, CI->getType()); 0
940 } ----
941 } ----
942 } ----
943 ----
944 if (uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src, CharSize)) { 0
945 Value *LenC = ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Len - 1); 0
946 // Fold strlen("xyz") -> 3 and strnlen("xyz", 2) -> 2 ----
947 // and strnlen("xyz", Bound) -> min(3, Bound) for nonconstant Bound. ----
948 if (Bound) 0
949 return B.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umin, LenC, Bound); 0
950 return LenC; 0
951 } ----
952 ----
953 if (Bound) 0
954 // Punt for strnlen for now. ----
955 return nullptr; 0
956 ----
957 // If s is a constant pointer pointing to a string literal, we can fold ----
958 // strlen(s + x) to strlen(s) - x, when x is known to be in the range ----
959 // [0, strlen(s)] or the string has a single null terminator '\0' at the end. ----
960 // We only try to simplify strlen when the pointer s points to an array ----
961 // of CharSize elements. Otherwise, we would need to scale the offset x before ----
962 // doing the subtraction. This will make the optimization more complex, and ----
963 // it's not very useful because calling strlen for a pointer of other types is ----
964 // very uncommon. ----
965 if (GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast(Src)) { 0
966 // TODO: Handle subobjects. ----
967 if (!isGEPBasedOnPointerToString(GEP, CharSize)) 0
968 return nullptr; 0
969 ----
970 ConstantDataArraySlice Slice; ----
971 if (getConstantDataArrayInfo(GEP->getOperand(0), Slice, CharSize)) { 0
972 uint64_t NullTermIdx; ----
973 if (Slice.Array == nullptr) { 0
974 NullTermIdx = 0; 0
975 } else { ----
976 NullTermIdx = ~((uint64_t)0); 0
977 for (uint64_t I = 0, E = Slice.Length; I < E; ++I) { 0
978 if (Slice.Array->getElementAsInteger(I + Slice.Offset) == 0) { 0
979 NullTermIdx = I; 0
980 break; 0
981 } ----
982 } ----
983 // If the string does not have '\0', leave it to strlen to compute ----
984 // its length. ----
985 if (NullTermIdx == ~((uint64_t)0)) 0
986 return nullptr; 0
987 } ----
988 ----
989 Value *Offset = GEP->getOperand(2); 0
990 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Offset, DL, 0, nullptr, CI, nullptr); 0
991 uint64_t ArrSize = ----
992 cast(GEP->getSourceElementType())->getNumElements(); 0
993 ----
994 // If Offset is not provably in the range [0, NullTermIdx], we can still ----
995 // optimize if we can prove that the program has undefined behavior when ----
996 // Offset is outside that range. That is the case when GEP->getOperand(0) ----
997 // is a pointer to an object whose memory extent is NullTermIdx+1. ----
998 if ((Known.isNonNegative() && Known.getMaxValue().ule(NullTermIdx)) || 0
999 (isa(GEP->getOperand(0)) && 0
1000 NullTermIdx == ArrSize - 1)) { 0
1001 Offset = B.CreateSExtOrTrunc(Offset, CI->getType()); 0
1002 return B.CreateSub(ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), NullTermIdx), 0
1003 Offset); 0
1004 } ----
1005 } 0
1006 } ----
1007 ----
1008 // strlen(x?"foo":"bars") --> x ? 3 : 4 ----
1009 if (SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast(Src)) { 0
1010 uint64_t LenTrue = GetStringLength(SI->getTrueValue(), CharSize); 0
1011 uint64_t LenFalse = GetStringLength(SI->getFalseValue(), CharSize); 0
1012 if (LenTrue && LenFalse) { 0
1013 ORE.emit([&]() { 0
1014 return OptimizationRemark("instcombine", "simplify-libcalls", CI) 0
1015 << "folded strlen(select) to select of constants"; 0
1016 }); ----
1017 return B.CreateSelect(SI->getCondition(), 0
1018 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), LenTrue - 1), 0
1019 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), LenFalse - 1)); 0
1020 } ----
1021 } ----
1022 ----
1023 return nullptr; 0
1024 } ----
1025 ----
1026 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrLen(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1027 if (Value *V = optimizeStringLength(CI, B, 8)) 0
1028 return V; 0
1029 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
1030 return nullptr; 0
1031 } ----
1032 ----
1033 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNLen(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1034 Value *Bound = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1035 if (Value *V = optimizeStringLength(CI, B, 8, Bound)) 0
1036 return V; 0
1037 ----
1038 if (isKnownNonZero(Bound, DL)) 0
1039 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
1040 return nullptr; 0
1041 } ----
1042 ----
1043 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeWcslen(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1044 Module &M = *CI->getModule(); 0
1045 unsigned WCharSize = TLI->getWCharSize(M) * 8; 0
1046 // We cannot perform this optimization without wchar_size metadata. ----
1047 if (WCharSize == 0) 0
1048 return nullptr; 0
1049 ----
1050 return optimizeStringLength(CI, B, WCharSize); 0
1051 } ----
1052 ----
1053 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrPBrk(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1054 StringRef S1, S2; 0
1055 bool HasS1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), S1); 0
1056 bool HasS2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), S2); 0
1057 ----
1058 // strpbrk(s, "") -> nullptr ----
1059 // strpbrk("", s) -> nullptr ----
1060 if ((HasS1 && S1.empty()) || (HasS2 && S2.empty())) 0
1061 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1062 ----
1063 // Constant folding. ----
1064 if (HasS1 && HasS2) { 0
1065 size_t I = S1.find_first_of(S2); 0
1066 if (I == StringRef::npos) // No match. 0
1067 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1068 ----
1069 return B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), CI->getArgOperand(0), 0
1070 B.getInt64(I), "strpbrk"); 0
1071 } ----
1072 ----
1073 // strpbrk(s, "a") -> strchr(s, 'a') ----
1074 if (HasS2 && S2.size() == 1) 0
1075 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrChr(CI->getArgOperand(0), S2[0], B, TLI)); 0
1076 ----
1077 return nullptr; 0
1078 } ----
1079 ----
1080 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrTo(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1081 Value *EndPtr = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1082 if (isa(EndPtr)) { 0
1083 // With a null EndPtr, this function won't capture the main argument. ----
1084 // It would be readonly too, except that it still may write to errno. ----
1085 CI->addParamAttr(0, Attribute::NoCapture); 0
1086 } ----
1087 ----
1088 return nullptr; 0
1089 } ----
1090 ----
1091 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrSpn(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1092 StringRef S1, S2; 0
1093 bool HasS1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), S1); 0
1094 bool HasS2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), S2); 0
1095 ----
1096 // strspn(s, "") -> 0 ----
1097 // strspn("", s) -> 0 ----
1098 if ((HasS1 && S1.empty()) || (HasS2 && S2.empty())) 0
1099 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1100 ----
1101 // Constant folding. ----
1102 if (HasS1 && HasS2) { 0
1103 size_t Pos = S1.find_first_not_of(S2); 0
1104 if (Pos == StringRef::npos) 0
1105 Pos = S1.size(); 0
1106 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Pos); 0
1107 } ----
1108 ----
1109 return nullptr; 0
1110 } ----
1111 ----
1112 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCSpn(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1113 StringRef S1, S2; 0
1114 bool HasS1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), S1); 0
1115 bool HasS2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), S2); 0
1116 ----
1117 // strcspn("", s) -> 0 ----
1118 if (HasS1 && S1.empty()) 0
1119 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1120 ----
1121 // Constant folding. ----
1122 if (HasS1 && HasS2) { 0
1123 size_t Pos = S1.find_first_of(S2); 0
1124 if (Pos == StringRef::npos) 0
1125 Pos = S1.size(); 0
1126 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Pos); 0
1127 } ----
1128 ----
1129 // strcspn(s, "") -> strlen(s) ----
1130 if (HasS2 && S2.empty()) 0
1131 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrLen(CI->getArgOperand(0), B, DL, TLI)); 0
1132 ----
1133 return nullptr; 0
1134 } ----
1135 ----
1136 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrStr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1137 // fold strstr(x, x) -> x. ----
1138 if (CI->getArgOperand(0) == CI->getArgOperand(1)) 0
1139 return B.CreateBitCast(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getType()); 0
1140 ----
1141 // fold strstr(a, b) == a -> strncmp(a, b, strlen(b)) == 0 ----
1142 if (isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(CI, CI->getArgOperand(0))) { 0
1143 Value *StrLen = emitStrLen(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, DL, TLI); 0
1144 if (!StrLen) 0
1145 return nullptr; 0
1146 Value *StrNCmp = emitStrNCmp(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), 0
1147 StrLen, B, DL, TLI); ----
1148 if (!StrNCmp) 0
1149 return nullptr; 0
1150 for (User *U : llvm::make_early_inc_range(CI->users())) { 0
1151 ICmpInst *Old = cast(U); 0
1152 Value *Cmp = ----
1153 B.CreateICmp(Old->getPredicate(), StrNCmp, 0
1154 ConstantInt::getNullValue(StrNCmp->getType()), "cmp"); 0
1155 replaceAllUsesWith(Old, Cmp); 0
1156 } ----
1157 return CI; 0
1158 } ----
1159 ----
1160 // See if either input string is a constant string. ----
1161 StringRef SearchStr, ToFindStr; 0
1162 bool HasStr1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), SearchStr); 0
1163 bool HasStr2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), ToFindStr); 0
1164 ----
1165 // fold strstr(x, "") -> x. ----
1166 if (HasStr2 && ToFindStr.empty()) 0
1167 return B.CreateBitCast(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getType()); 0
1168 ----
1169 // If both strings are known, constant fold it. ----
1170 if (HasStr1 && HasStr2) { 0
1171 size_t Offset = SearchStr.find(ToFindStr); 0
1172 ----
1173 if (Offset == StringRef::npos) // strstr("foo", "bar") -> null 0
1174 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1175 ----
1176 // strstr("abcd", "bc") -> gep((char*)"abcd", 1) ----
1177 Value *Result = castToCStr(CI->getArgOperand(0), B); 0
1178 Result = ----
1179 B.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(B.getInt8Ty(), Result, Offset, "strstr"); 0
1180 return B.CreateBitCast(Result, CI->getType()); 0
1181 } ----
1182 ----
1183 // fold strstr(x, "y") -> strchr(x, 'y'). ----
1184 if (HasStr2 && ToFindStr.size() == 1) { 0
1185 Value *StrChr = emitStrChr(CI->getArgOperand(0), ToFindStr[0], B, TLI); 0
1186 return StrChr ? B.CreateBitCast(StrChr, CI->getType()) : nullptr; 0
1187 } ----
1188 ----
1189 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, {0, 1}); 0
1190 return nullptr; 0
1191 } ----
1192 ----
1193 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemRChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1194 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1195 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1196 annotateNonNullAndDereferenceable(CI, 0, Size, DL); 0
1197 Value *CharVal = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1198 ConstantInt *LenC = dyn_cast(Size); 0
1199 Value *NullPtr = Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1200 ----
1201 if (LenC) { 0
1202 if (LenC->isZero()) 0
1203 // Fold memrchr(x, y, 0) --> null. ----
1204 return NullPtr; 0
1205 ----
1206 if (LenC->isOne()) { 0
1207 // Fold memrchr(x, y, 1) --> *x == y ? x : null for any x and y, ----
1208 // constant or otherwise. ----
1209 Value *Val = B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, "memrchr.char0"); 0
1210 // Slice off the character's high end bits. ----
1211 CharVal = B.CreateTrunc(CharVal, B.getInt8Ty()); 0
1212 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpEQ(Val, CharVal, "memrchr.char0cmp"); 0
1213 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, SrcStr, NullPtr, "memrchr.sel"); 0
1214 } ----
1215 } ----
1216 ----
1217 StringRef Str; 0
1218 if (!getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str, /*TrimAtNul=*/false)) 0
1219 return nullptr; 0
1220 ----
1221 if (Str.size() == 0) 0
1222 // If the array is empty fold memrchr(A, C, N) to null for any value ----
1223 // of C and N on the basis that the only valid value of N is zero ----
1224 // (otherwise the call is undefined). ----
1225 return NullPtr; 0
1226 ----
1227 uint64_t EndOff = UINT64_MAX; 0
1228 if (LenC) { 0
1229 EndOff = LenC->getZExtValue(); 0
1230 if (Str.size() < EndOff) 0
1231 // Punt out-of-bounds accesses to sanitizers and/or libc. ----
1232 return nullptr; 0
1233 } ----
1234 ----
1235 if (ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast(CharVal)) { 0
1236 // Fold memrchr(S, C, N) for a constant C. ----
1237 size_t Pos = Str.rfind(CharC->getZExtValue(), EndOff); 0
1238 if (Pos == StringRef::npos) 0
1239 // When the character is not in the source array fold the result ----
1240 // to null regardless of Size. ----
1241 return NullPtr; 0
1242 ----
1243 if (LenC) 0
1244 // Fold memrchr(s, c, N) --> s + Pos for constant N > Pos. ----
1245 return B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, B.getInt64(Pos)); 0
1246 ----
1247 if (Str.find(Str[Pos]) == Pos) { 0
1248 // When there is just a single occurrence of C in S, i.e., the one ----
1249 // in Str[Pos], fold ----
1250 // memrchr(s, c, N) --> N <= Pos ? null : s + Pos ----
1251 // for nonconstant N. ----
1252 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpULE(Size, ConstantInt::get(Size->getType(), Pos), 0
1253 "memrchr.cmp"); ----
1254 Value *SrcPlus = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, 0
1255 B.getInt64(Pos), "memrchr.ptr_plus"); 0
1256 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, NullPtr, SrcPlus, "memrchr.sel"); 0
1257 } ----
1258 } ----
1259 ----
1260 // Truncate the string to search at most EndOff characters. ----
1261 Str = Str.substr(0, EndOff); 0
1262 if (Str.find_first_not_of(Str[0]) != StringRef::npos) 0
1263 return nullptr; 0
1264 ----
1265 // If the source array consists of all equal characters, then for any ----
1266 // C and N (whether in bounds or not), fold memrchr(S, C, N) to ----
1267 // N != 0 && *S == C ? S + N - 1 : null ----
1268 Type *SizeTy = Size->getType(); 0
1269 Type *Int8Ty = B.getInt8Ty(); 0
1270 Value *NNeZ = B.CreateICmpNE(Size, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0)); 0
1271 // Slice off the sought character's high end bits. ----
1272 CharVal = B.CreateTrunc(CharVal, Int8Ty); 0
1273 Value *CEqS0 = B.CreateICmpEQ(ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Str[0]), CharVal); 0
1274 Value *And = B.CreateLogicalAnd(NNeZ, CEqS0); 0
1275 Value *SizeM1 = B.CreateSub(Size, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 1)); 0
1276 Value *SrcPlus = ----
1277 B.CreateInBoundsGEP(Int8Ty, SrcStr, SizeM1, "memrchr.ptr_plus"); 0
1278 return B.CreateSelect(And, SrcPlus, NullPtr, "memrchr.sel"); 0
1279 } ----
1280 ----
1281 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1282 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1283 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1284 ----
1285 if (isKnownNonZero(Size, DL)) { 0
1286 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
1287 if (isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(CI, SrcStr)) 0
1288 return memChrToCharCompare(CI, Size, B, DL); 0
1289 } ----
1290 ----
1291 Value *CharVal = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1292 ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast(CharVal); 0
1293 ConstantInt *LenC = dyn_cast(Size); 0
1294 Value *NullPtr = Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1295 ----
1296 // memchr(x, y, 0) -> null ----
1297 if (LenC) { 0
1298 if (LenC->isZero()) 0
1299 return NullPtr; 0
1300 ----
1301 if (LenC->isOne()) { 0
1302 // Fold memchr(x, y, 1) --> *x == y ? x : null for any x and y, ----
1303 // constant or otherwise. ----
1304 Value *Val = B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, "memchr.char0"); 0
1305 // Slice off the character's high end bits. ----
1306 CharVal = B.CreateTrunc(CharVal, B.getInt8Ty()); 0
1307 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpEQ(Val, CharVal, "memchr.char0cmp"); 0
1308 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, SrcStr, NullPtr, "memchr.sel"); 0
1309 } ----
1310 } ----
1311 ----
1312 StringRef Str; 0
1313 if (!getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str, /*TrimAtNul=*/false)) 0
1314 return nullptr; 0
1315 ----
1316 if (CharC) { 0
1317 size_t Pos = Str.find(CharC->getZExtValue()); 0
1318 if (Pos == StringRef::npos) 0
1319 // When the character is not in the source array fold the result ----
1320 // to null regardless of Size. ----
1321 return NullPtr; 0
1322 ----
1323 // Fold memchr(s, c, n) -> n <= Pos ? null : s + Pos ----
1324 // When the constant Size is less than or equal to the character ----
1325 // position also fold the result to null. ----
1326 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmpULE(Size, ConstantInt::get(Size->getType(), Pos), 0
1327 "memchr.cmp"); ----
1328 Value *SrcPlus = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, B.getInt64(Pos), 0
1329 "memchr.ptr"); ----
1330 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, NullPtr, SrcPlus); 0
1331 } ----
1332 ----
1333 if (Str.size() == 0) 0
1334 // If the array is empty fold memchr(A, C, N) to null for any value ----
1335 // of C and N on the basis that the only valid value of N is zero ----
1336 // (otherwise the call is undefined). ----
1337 return NullPtr; 0
1338 ----
1339 if (LenC) 0
1340 Str = substr(Str, LenC->getZExtValue()); 0
1341 ----
1342 size_t Pos = Str.find_first_not_of(Str[0]); 0
1343 if (Pos == StringRef::npos 0
1344 || Str.find_first_not_of(Str[Pos], Pos) == StringRef::npos) { 0
1345 // If the source array consists of at most two consecutive sequences ----
1346 // of the same characters, then for any C and N (whether in bounds or ----
1347 // not), fold memchr(S, C, N) to ----
1348 // N != 0 && *S == C ? S : null ----
1349 // or for the two sequences to: ----
1350 // N != 0 && *S == C ? S : (N > Pos && S[Pos] == C ? S + Pos : null) ----
1351 // ^Sel2 ^Sel1 are denoted above. ----
1352 // The latter makes it also possible to fold strchr() calls with strings ----
1353 // of the same characters. ----
1354 Type *SizeTy = Size->getType(); 0
1355 Type *Int8Ty = B.getInt8Ty(); 0
1356 ----
1357 // Slice off the sought character's high end bits. ----
1358 CharVal = B.CreateTrunc(CharVal, Int8Ty); 0
1359 ----
1360 Value *Sel1 = NullPtr; 0
1361 if (Pos != StringRef::npos) { 0
1362 // Handle two consecutive sequences of the same characters. ----
1363 Value *PosVal = ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, Pos); 0
1364 Value *StrPos = ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Str[Pos]); 0
1365 Value *CEqSPos = B.CreateICmpEQ(CharVal, StrPos); 0
1366 Value *NGtPos = B.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT, Size, PosVal); 0
1367 Value *And = B.CreateAnd(CEqSPos, NGtPos); 0
1368 Value *SrcPlus = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, PosVal); 0
1369 Sel1 = B.CreateSelect(And, SrcPlus, NullPtr, "memchr.sel1"); 0
1370 } ----
1371 ----
1372 Value *Str0 = ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Str[0]); 0
1373 Value *CEqS0 = B.CreateICmpEQ(Str0, CharVal); 0
1374 Value *NNeZ = B.CreateICmpNE(Size, ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 0)); 0
1375 Value *And = B.CreateAnd(NNeZ, CEqS0); 0
1376 return B.CreateSelect(And, SrcStr, Sel1, "memchr.sel2"); 0
1377 } ----
1378 ----
1379 if (!LenC) { 0
1380 if (isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(CI, SrcStr)) 0
1381 // S is dereferenceable so it's safe to load from it and fold ----
1382 // memchr(S, C, N) == S to N && *S == C for any C and N. ----
1383 // TODO: This is safe even even for nonconstant S. ----
1384 return memChrToCharCompare(CI, Size, B, DL); 0
1385 ----
1386 // From now on we need a constant length and constant array. ----
1387 return nullptr; 0
1388 } ----
1389 ----
1390 bool OptForSize = CI->getFunction()->hasOptSize() || 0
1391 llvm::shouldOptimizeForSize(CI->getParent(), PSI, BFI, 0
1392 PGSOQueryType::IRPass); 0
1393 ----
1394 // If the char is variable but the input str and length are not we can turn ----
1395 // this memchr call into a simple bit field test. Of course this only works ----
1396 // when the return value is only checked against null. ----
1397 // ----
1398 // It would be really nice to reuse switch lowering here but we can't change ----
1399 // the CFG at this point. ----
1400 // ----
1401 // memchr("\r\n", C, 2) != nullptr -> (1 << C & ((1 << '\r') | (1 << '\n'))) ----
1402 // != 0 ----
1403 // after bounds check. ----
1404 if (OptForSize || Str.empty() || !isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI)) 0
1405 return nullptr; 0
1406 ----
1407 unsigned char Max = ----
1408 *std::max_element(reinterpret_cast(Str.begin()), 0
1409 reinterpret_cast(Str.end())); 0
1410 ----
1411 // Make sure the bit field we're about to create fits in a register on the ----
1412 // target. ----
1413 // FIXME: On a 64 bit architecture this prevents us from using the ----
1414 // interesting range of alpha ascii chars. We could do better by emitting ----
1415 // two bitfields or shifting the range by 64 if no lower chars are used. ----
1416 if (!DL.fitsInLegalInteger(Max + 1)) { 0
1417 // Build chain of ORs ----
1418 // Transform: ----
1419 // memchr("abcd", C, 4) != nullptr ----
1420 // to: ----
1421 // (C == 'a' || C == 'b' || C == 'c' || C == 'd') != 0 ----
1422 std::string SortedStr = Str.str(); 0
1423 llvm::sort(SortedStr); 0
1424 // Compute the number of of non-contiguous ranges. ----
1425 unsigned NonContRanges = 1; 0
1426 for (size_t i = 1; i < SortedStr.size(); ++i) { 0
1427 if (SortedStr[i] > SortedStr[i - 1] + 1) { 0
1428 NonContRanges++; 0
1429 } ----
1430 } ----
1431 ----
1432 // Restrict this optimization to profitable cases with one or two range ----
1433 // checks. ----
1434 if (NonContRanges > 2) 0
1435 return nullptr; 0
1436 ----
1437 SmallVector CharCompares; 0
1438 for (unsigned char C : SortedStr) 0
1439 CharCompares.push_back( 0
1440 B.CreateICmpEQ(CharVal, ConstantInt::get(CharVal->getType(), C))); 0
1441 ----
1442 return B.CreateIntToPtr(B.CreateOr(CharCompares), CI->getType()); 0
1443 } 0
1444 ----
1445 // For the bit field use a power-of-2 type with at least 8 bits to avoid ----
1446 // creating unnecessary illegal types. ----
1447 unsigned char Width = NextPowerOf2(std::max((unsigned char)7, Max)); 0
1448 ----
1449 // Now build the bit field. ----
1450 APInt Bitfield(Width, 0); 0
1451 for (char C : Str) 0
1452 Bitfield.setBit((unsigned char)C); 0
1453 Value *BitfieldC = B.getInt(Bitfield); 0
1454 ----
1455 // Adjust width of "C" to the bitfield width, then mask off the high bits. ----
1456 Value *C = B.CreateZExtOrTrunc(CharVal, BitfieldC->getType()); 0
1457 C = B.CreateAnd(C, B.getIntN(Width, 0xFF)); 0
1458 ----
1459 // First check that the bit field access is within bounds. ----
1460 Value *Bounds = B.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, C, B.getIntN(Width, Width), 0
1461 "memchr.bounds"); ----
1462 ----
1463 // Create code that checks if the given bit is set in the field. ----
1464 Value *Shl = B.CreateShl(B.getIntN(Width, 1ULL), C); 0
1465 Value *Bits = B.CreateIsNotNull(B.CreateAnd(Shl, BitfieldC), "memchr.bits"); 0
1466 ----
1467 // Finally merge both checks and cast to pointer type. The inttoptr ----
1468 // implicitly zexts the i1 to intptr type. ----
1469 return B.CreateIntToPtr(B.CreateLogicalAnd(Bounds, Bits, "memchr"), 0
1470 CI->getType()); 0
1471 } 0
1472 ----
1473 // Optimize a memcmp or, when StrNCmp is true, strncmp call CI with constant ----
1474 // arrays LHS and RHS and nonconstant Size. ----
1475 static Value *optimizeMemCmpVarSize(CallInst *CI, Value *LHS, Value *RHS, 0
1476 Value *Size, bool StrNCmp, ----
1477 IRBuilderBase &B, const DataLayout &DL) { ----
1478 if (LHS == RHS) // memcmp(s,s,x) -> 0 0
1479 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1480 ----
1481 StringRef LStr, RStr; 0
1482 if (!getConstantStringInfo(LHS, LStr, /*TrimAtNul=*/false) || 0
1483 !getConstantStringInfo(RHS, RStr, /*TrimAtNul=*/false)) 0
1484 return nullptr; 0
1485 ----
1486 // If the contents of both constant arrays are known, fold a call to ----
1487 // memcmp(A, B, N) to ----
1488 // N <= Pos ? 0 : (A < B ? -1 : B < A ? +1 : 0) ----
1489 // where Pos is the first mismatch between A and B, determined below. ----
1490 ----
1491 uint64_t Pos = 0; 0
1492 Value *Zero = ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
1493 for (uint64_t MinSize = std::min(LStr.size(), RStr.size()); ; ++Pos) { 0
1494 if (Pos == MinSize || 0
1495 (StrNCmp && (LStr[Pos] == '\0' && RStr[Pos] == '\0'))) { 0
1496 // One array is a leading part of the other of equal or greater ----
1497 // size, or for strncmp, the arrays are equal strings. ----
1498 // Fold the result to zero. Size is assumed to be in bounds, since ----
1499 // otherwise the call would be undefined. ----
1500 return Zero; 0
1501 } ----
1502 ----
1503 if (LStr[Pos] != RStr[Pos]) 0
1504 break; 0
1505 } ----
1506 ----
1507 // Normalize the result. ----
1508 typedef unsigned char UChar; ----
1509 int IRes = UChar(LStr[Pos]) < UChar(RStr[Pos]) ? -1 : 1; 0
1510 Value *MaxSize = ConstantInt::get(Size->getType(), Pos); 0
1511 Value *Cmp = B.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE, Size, MaxSize); 0
1512 Value *Res = ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), IRes); 0
1513 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, Zero, Res); 0
1514 } ----
1515 ----
1516 // Optimize a memcmp call CI with constant size Len. ----
1517 static Value *optimizeMemCmpConstantSize(CallInst *CI, Value *LHS, Value *RHS, 0
1518 uint64_t Len, IRBuilderBase &B, ----
1519 const DataLayout &DL) { ----
1520 if (Len == 0) // memcmp(s1,s2,0) -> 0 0
1521 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1522 ----
1523 // memcmp(S1,S2,1) -> *(unsigned char*)LHS - *(unsigned char*)RHS ----
1524 if (Len == 1) { 0
1525 Value *LHSV = ----
1526 B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), castToCStr(LHS, B), "lhsc"), 0
1527 CI->getType(), "lhsv"); ----
1528 Value *RHSV = ----
1529 B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), castToCStr(RHS, B), "rhsc"), 0
1530 CI->getType(), "rhsv"); ----
1531 return B.CreateSub(LHSV, RHSV, "chardiff"); 0
1532 } ----
1533 ----
1534 // memcmp(S1,S2,N/8)==0 -> (*(intN_t*)S1 != *(intN_t*)S2)==0 ----
1535 // TODO: The case where both inputs are constants does not need to be limited ----
1536 // to legal integers or equality comparison. See block below this. ----
1537 if (DL.isLegalInteger(Len * 8) && isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI)) { 0
1538 IntegerType *IntType = IntegerType::get(CI->getContext(), Len * 8); 0
1539 Align PrefAlignment = DL.getPrefTypeAlign(IntType); 0
1540 ----
1541 // First, see if we can fold either argument to a constant. ----
1542 Value *LHSV = nullptr; 0
1543 if (auto *LHSC = dyn_cast(LHS)) 0
1544 LHSV = ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(LHSC, IntType, DL); 0
1545 ----
1546 Value *RHSV = nullptr; 0
1547 if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast(RHS)) 0
1548 RHSV = ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(RHSC, IntType, DL); 0
1549 ----
1550 // Don't generate unaligned loads. If either source is constant data, ----
1551 // alignment doesn't matter for that source because there is no load. ----
1552 if ((LHSV || getKnownAlignment(LHS, DL, CI) >= PrefAlignment) && 0
1553 (RHSV || getKnownAlignment(RHS, DL, CI) >= PrefAlignment)) { 0
1554 if (!LHSV) 0
1555 LHSV = B.CreateLoad(IntType, LHS, "lhsv"); 0
1556 if (!RHSV) 0
1557 RHSV = B.CreateLoad(IntType, RHS, "rhsv"); 0
1558 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateICmpNE(LHSV, RHSV), CI->getType(), "memcmp"); 0
1559 } ----
1560 } ----
1561 ----
1562 return nullptr; 0
1563 } ----
1564 ----
1565 // Most simplifications for memcmp also apply to bcmp. ----
1566 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemCmpBCmpCommon(CallInst *CI, 0
1567 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
1568 Value *LHS = CI->getArgOperand(0), *RHS = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1569 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1570 ----
1571 annotateNonNullAndDereferenceable(CI, {0, 1}, Size, DL); 0
1572 ----
1573 if (Value *Res = optimizeMemCmpVarSize(CI, LHS, RHS, Size, false, B, DL)) 0
1574 return Res; 0
1575 ----
1576 // Handle constant Size. ----
1577 ConstantInt *LenC = dyn_cast(Size); 0
1578 if (!LenC) 0
1579 return nullptr; 0
1580 ----
1581 return optimizeMemCmpConstantSize(CI, LHS, RHS, LenC->getZExtValue(), B, DL); 0
1582 } ----
1583 ----
1584 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1585 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1586 if (Value *V = optimizeMemCmpBCmpCommon(CI, B)) 0
1587 return V; 0
1588 ----
1589 // memcmp(x, y, Len) == 0 -> bcmp(x, y, Len) == 0 ----
1590 // bcmp can be more efficient than memcmp because it only has to know that ----
1591 // there is a difference, not how different one is to the other. ----
1592 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_bcmp) && 0
1593 isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI)) { 0
1594 Value *LHS = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1595 Value *RHS = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1596 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1597 return copyFlags(*CI, emitBCmp(LHS, RHS, Size, B, DL, TLI)); 0
1598 } ----
1599 ----
1600 return nullptr; 0
1601 } ----
1602 ----
1603 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeBCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1604 return optimizeMemCmpBCmpCommon(CI, B); 0
1605 } ----
1606 ----
1607 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1608 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1609 annotateNonNullAndDereferenceable(CI, {0, 1}, Size, DL); 0
1610 if (isa(CI)) 0
1611 return nullptr; 0
1612 ----
1613 // memcpy(x, y, n) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 x, align 1 y, n) ----
1614 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemCpy(CI->getArgOperand(0), Align(1), 0
1615 CI->getArgOperand(1), Align(1), Size); ----
1616 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
1617 return CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1618 } ----
1619 ----
1620 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemCCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1621 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1622 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1623 ConstantInt *StopChar = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(2)); 0
1624 ConstantInt *N = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(3)); 0
1625 StringRef SrcStr; 0
1626 if (CI->use_empty() && Dst == Src) 0
1627 return Dst; 0
1628 // memccpy(d, s, c, 0) -> nullptr ----
1629 if (N) { 0
1630 if (N->isNullValue()) 0
1631 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1632 if (!getConstantStringInfo(Src, SrcStr, /*TrimAtNul=*/false) || 0
1633 // TODO: Handle zeroinitializer. ----
1634 !StopChar) ----
1635 return nullptr; 0
1636 } else { ----
1637 return nullptr; 0
1638 } ----
1639 ----
1640 // Wrap arg 'c' of type int to char ----
1641 size_t Pos = SrcStr.find(StopChar->getSExtValue() & 0xFF); 0
1642 if (Pos == StringRef::npos) { 0
1643 if (N->getZExtValue() <= SrcStr.size()) { 0
1644 copyFlags(*CI, B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), 0
1645 CI->getArgOperand(3))); ----
1646 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1647 } ----
1648 return nullptr; 0
1649 } ----
1650 ----
1651 Value *NewN = ----
1652 ConstantInt::get(N->getType(), std::min(uint64_t(Pos + 1), N->getZExtValue())); 0
1653 // memccpy -> llvm.memcpy ----
1654 copyFlags(*CI, B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), Src, Align(1), NewN)); 0
1655 return Pos + 1 <= N->getZExtValue() 0
1656 ? B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, NewN) 0
1657 : Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()); 0
1658 } ----
1659 ----
1660 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemPCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1661 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1662 Value *N = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1663 // mempcpy(x, y, n) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 x, align 1 y, n), x + n ----
1664 CallInst *NewCI = ----
1665 B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, Align(1), CI->getArgOperand(1), Align(1), N); 0
1666 // Propagate attributes, but memcpy has no return value, so make sure that ----
1667 // any return attributes are compliant. ----
1668 // TODO: Attach return value attributes to the 1st operand to preserve them? ----
1669 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
1670 return B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, N); 0
1671 } ----
1672 ----
1673 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemMove(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1674 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1675 annotateNonNullAndDereferenceable(CI, {0, 1}, Size, DL); 0
1676 if (isa(CI)) 0
1677 return nullptr; 0
1678 ----
1679 // memmove(x, y, n) -> llvm.memmove(align 1 x, align 1 y, n) ----
1680 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemMove(CI->getArgOperand(0), Align(1), 0
1681 CI->getArgOperand(1), Align(1), Size); ----
1682 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
1683 return CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1684 } ----
1685 ----
1686 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemSet(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1687 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1688 annotateNonNullAndDereferenceable(CI, 0, Size, DL); 0
1689 if (isa(CI)) 0
1690 return nullptr; 0
1691 ----
1692 // memset(p, v, n) -> llvm.memset(align 1 p, v, n) ----
1693 Value *Val = B.CreateIntCast(CI->getArgOperand(1), B.getInt8Ty(), false); 0
1694 CallInst *NewCI = B.CreateMemSet(CI->getArgOperand(0), Val, Size, Align(1)); 0
1695 mergeAttributesAndFlags(NewCI, *CI); 0
1696 return CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1697 } ----
1698 ----
1699 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeRealloc(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1700 if (isa(CI->getArgOperand(0))) 0
1701 return copyFlags(*CI, emitMalloc(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, DL, TLI)); 0
1702 ----
1703 return nullptr; 0
1704 } ----
1705 ----
1706 // When enabled, replace operator new() calls marked with a hot or cold memprof ----
1707 // attribute with an operator new() call that takes a __hot_cold_t parameter. ----
1708 // Currently this is supported by the open source version of tcmalloc, see: ----
1709 // https://github.com/google/tcmalloc/blob/master/tcmalloc/new_extension.h ----
1710 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeNew(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1711 LibFunc &Func) { ----
1712 if (!OptimizeHotColdNew) 0
1713 return nullptr; 0
1714 ----
1715 uint8_t HotCold; ----
1716 if (CI->getAttributes().getFnAttr("memprof").getValueAsString() == "cold") 0
1717 HotCold = ColdNewHintValue; 0
1718 else if (CI->getAttributes().getFnAttr("memprof").getValueAsString() == "hot") 0
1719 HotCold = HotNewHintValue; 0
1720 else ----
1721 return nullptr; 0
1722 ----
1723 switch (Func) { 0
1724 case LibFunc_Znwm: 0
1725 return emitHotColdNew(CI->getArgOperand(0), B, TLI, 0
1726 LibFunc_Znwm12__hot_cold_t, HotCold); 0
1727 case LibFunc_Znam: 0
1728 return emitHotColdNew(CI->getArgOperand(0), B, TLI, 0
1729 LibFunc_Znam12__hot_cold_t, HotCold); 0
1730 case LibFunc_ZnwmRKSt9nothrow_t: 0
1731 return emitHotColdNewNoThrow(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), B, 0
1732 TLI, LibFunc_ZnwmRKSt9nothrow_t12__hot_cold_t, ----
1733 HotCold); 0
1734 case LibFunc_ZnamRKSt9nothrow_t: 0
1735 return emitHotColdNewNoThrow(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), B, 0
1736 TLI, LibFunc_ZnamRKSt9nothrow_t12__hot_cold_t, ----
1737 HotCold); 0
1738 case LibFunc_ZnwmSt11align_val_t: 0
1739 return emitHotColdNewAligned(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), B, 0
1740 TLI, LibFunc_ZnwmSt11align_val_t12__hot_cold_t, ----
1741 HotCold); 0
1742 case LibFunc_ZnamSt11align_val_t: 0
1743 return emitHotColdNewAligned(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), B, 0
1744 TLI, LibFunc_ZnamSt11align_val_t12__hot_cold_t, ----
1745 HotCold); 0
1746 case LibFunc_ZnwmSt11align_val_tRKSt9nothrow_t: 0
1747 return emitHotColdNewAlignedNoThrow( 0
1748 CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), CI->getArgOperand(2), B, ----
1749 TLI, LibFunc_ZnwmSt11align_val_tRKSt9nothrow_t12__hot_cold_t, HotCold); 0
1750 case LibFunc_ZnamSt11align_val_tRKSt9nothrow_t: 0
1751 return emitHotColdNewAlignedNoThrow( 0
1752 CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), CI->getArgOperand(2), B, ----
1753 TLI, LibFunc_ZnamSt11align_val_tRKSt9nothrow_t12__hot_cold_t, HotCold); 0
1754 default: 0
1755 return nullptr; 0
1756 } ----
1757 } ----
