1759 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1760 // Math Library Optimizations ----
1761 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1762 ----
1763 // Replace a libcall \p CI with a call to intrinsic \p IID ----
1764 static Value *replaceUnaryCall(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1765 Intrinsic::ID IID) { ----
1766 // Propagate fast-math flags from the existing call to the new call. ----
1767 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
1768 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags()); 0
1769 ----
1770 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1771 Value *V = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1772 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, IID, CI->getType()); 0
1773 CallInst *NewCall = B.CreateCall(F, V); 0
1774 NewCall->takeName(CI); 0
1775 return copyFlags(*CI, NewCall); 0
1776 } 0
1777 ----
1778 /// Return a variant of Val with float type. ----
1779 /// Currently this works in two cases: If Val is an FPExtension of a float ----
1780 /// value to something bigger, simply return the operand. ----
1781 /// If Val is a ConstantFP but can be converted to a float ConstantFP without ----
1782 /// loss of precision do so. ----
1783 static Value *valueHasFloatPrecision(Value *Val) { 0
1784 if (FPExtInst *Cast = dyn_cast(Val)) { 0
1785 Value *Op = Cast->getOperand(0); 0
1786 if (Op->getType()->isFloatTy()) 0
1787 return Op; 0
1788 } ----
1789 if (ConstantFP *Const = dyn_cast(Val)) { 0
1790 APFloat F = Const->getValueAPF(); 0
1791 bool losesInfo; ----
1792 (void)F.convert(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, 0
1793 &losesInfo); ----
1794 if (!losesInfo) 0
1795 return ConstantFP::get(Const->getContext(), F); 0
1796 } 0
1797 return nullptr; 0
1798 } ----
1799 ----
1800 /// Shrink double -> float functions. ----
1801 static Value *optimizeDoubleFP(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1802 bool isBinary, const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI, ----
1803 bool isPrecise = false) { ----
1804 Function *CalleeFn = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
1805 if (!CI->getType()->isDoubleTy() || !CalleeFn) 0
1806 return nullptr; 0
1807 ----
1808 // If not all the uses of the function are converted to float, then bail out. ----
1809 // This matters if the precision of the result is more important than the ----
1810 // precision of the arguments. ----
1811 if (isPrecise) 0
1812 for (User *U : CI->users()) { 0
1813 FPTruncInst *Cast = dyn_cast(U); 0
1814 if (!Cast || !Cast->getType()->isFloatTy()) 0
1815 return nullptr; 0
1816 } ----
1817 ----
1818 // If this is something like 'g((double) float)', convert to 'gf(float)'. ----
1819 Value *V[2]; ----
1820 V[0] = valueHasFloatPrecision(CI->getArgOperand(0)); 0
1821 V[1] = isBinary ? valueHasFloatPrecision(CI->getArgOperand(1)) : nullptr; 0
1822 if (!V[0] || (isBinary && !V[1])) 0
1823 return nullptr; 0
1824 ----
1825 // If call isn't an intrinsic, check that it isn't within a function with the ----
1826 // same name as the float version of this call, otherwise the result is an ----
1827 // infinite loop. For example, from MinGW-w64: ----
1828 // ----
1829 // float expf(float val) { return (float) exp((double) val); } ----
1830 StringRef CalleeName = CalleeFn->getName(); 0
1831 bool IsIntrinsic = CalleeFn->isIntrinsic(); 0
1832 if (!IsIntrinsic) { 0
1833 StringRef CallerName = CI->getFunction()->getName(); 0
1834 if (!CallerName.empty() && CallerName.back() == 'f' && 0
1835 CallerName.size() == (CalleeName.size() + 1) && 0
1836 CallerName.startswith(CalleeName)) 0
1837 return nullptr; 0
1838 } ----
1839 ----
1840 // Propagate the math semantics from the current function to the new function. ----
1841 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
1842 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags()); 0
1843 ----
1844 // g((double) float) -> (double) gf(float) ----
1845 Value *R; ----
1846 if (IsIntrinsic) { 0
1847 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1848 Intrinsic::ID IID = CalleeFn->getIntrinsicID(); 0
1849 Function *Fn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, IID, B.getFloatTy()); 0
1850 R = isBinary ? B.CreateCall(Fn, V) : B.CreateCall(Fn, V[0]); 0
1851 } else { ----
1852 AttributeList CalleeAttrs = CalleeFn->getAttributes(); 0
1853 R = isBinary ? emitBinaryFloatFnCall(V[0], V[1], TLI, CalleeName, B, 0
1854 CalleeAttrs) ----
1855 : emitUnaryFloatFnCall(V[0], TLI, CalleeName, B, CalleeAttrs); 0
1856 } ----
1857 return B.CreateFPExt(R, B.getDoubleTy()); 0
1858 } 0
1859 ----
1860 /// Shrink double -> float for unary functions. ----
1861 static Value *optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1862 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI, ----
1863 bool isPrecise = false) { ----
1864 return optimizeDoubleFP(CI, B, false, TLI, isPrecise); 0
1865 } ----
1866 ----
1867 /// Shrink double -> float for binary functions. ----
1868 static Value *optimizeBinaryDoubleFP(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1869 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI, ----
1870 bool isPrecise = false) { ----
1871 return optimizeDoubleFP(CI, B, true, TLI, isPrecise); 0
1872 } ----
1873 ----
1874 // cabs(z) -> sqrt((creal(z)*creal(z)) + (cimag(z)*cimag(z))) ----
1875 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCAbs(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1876 if (!CI->isFast()) 0
1877 return nullptr; 0
1878 ----
1879 // Propagate fast-math flags from the existing call to new instructions. ----
1880 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
1881 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags()); 0
1882 ----
1883 Value *Real, *Imag; ----
1884 if (CI->arg_size() == 1) { 0
1885 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1886 assert(Op->getType()->isArrayTy() && "Unexpected signature for cabs!"); 0
1887 Real = B.CreateExtractValue(Op, 0, "real"); 0
1888 Imag = B.CreateExtractValue(Op, 1, "imag"); 0
1889 } else { ----
1890 assert(CI->arg_size() == 2 && "Unexpected signature for cabs!"); 0
1891 Real = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1892 Imag = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1893 } ----
1894 ----
1895 Value *RealReal = B.CreateFMul(Real, Real); 0
1896 Value *ImagImag = B.CreateFMul(Imag, Imag); 0
1897 ----
1898 Function *FSqrt = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getModule(), Intrinsic::sqrt, 0
1899 CI->getType()); 0
1900 return copyFlags( 0
1901 *CI, B.CreateCall(FSqrt, B.CreateFAdd(RealReal, ImagImag), "cabs")); 0
1902 } 0
1903 ----
1904 static Value *optimizeTrigReflections(CallInst *Call, LibFunc Func, 0
1905 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
1906 if (!isa(Call)) 0
1907 return nullptr; 0
1908 ----
1909 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
1910 B.setFastMathFlags(Call->getFastMathFlags()); 0
1911 ----
1912 // TODO: Can this be shared to also handle LLVM intrinsics? ----
1913 Value *X; ----
1914 switch (Func) { 0
1915 case LibFunc_sin: 0
1916 case LibFunc_sinf: ----
1917 case LibFunc_sinl: ----
1918 case LibFunc_tan: ----
1919 case LibFunc_tanf: ----
1920 case LibFunc_tanl: ----
1921 // sin(-X) --> -sin(X) ----
1922 // tan(-X) --> -tan(X) ----
1923 if (match(Call->getArgOperand(0), m_OneUse(m_FNeg(m_Value(X))))) 0
1924 return B.CreateFNeg( 0
1925 copyFlags(*Call, B.CreateCall(Call->getCalledFunction(), X))); 0
1926 break; 0
1927 case LibFunc_cos: 0
1928 case LibFunc_cosf: ----
1929 case LibFunc_cosl: ----
1930 // cos(-X) --> cos(X) ----
1931 if (match(Call->getArgOperand(0), m_FNeg(m_Value(X)))) 0
1932 return copyFlags(*Call, 0
1933 B.CreateCall(Call->getCalledFunction(), X, "cos")); 0
1934 break; 0
1935 default: 0
1936 break; 0
1937 } ----
1938 return nullptr; 0
1939 } 0
1940 ----
1941 // Return a properly extended integer (DstWidth bits wide) if the operation is ----
1942 // an itofp. ----
1943 static Value *getIntToFPVal(Value *I2F, IRBuilderBase &B, unsigned DstWidth) { 0
1944 if (isa(I2F) || isa(I2F)) { 0
1945 Value *Op = cast(I2F)->getOperand(0); 0
1946 // Make sure that the exponent fits inside an "int" of size DstWidth, ----
1947 // thus avoiding any range issues that FP has not. ----
1948 unsigned BitWidth = Op->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(); 0
1949 if (BitWidth < DstWidth || 0
1950 (BitWidth == DstWidth && isa(I2F))) 0
1951 return isa(I2F) ? B.CreateSExt(Op, B.getIntNTy(DstWidth)) 0
1952 : B.CreateZExt(Op, B.getIntNTy(DstWidth)); 0
1953 } ----
1954 ----
1955 return nullptr; 0
1956 } ----
1957 ----
1958 /// Use exp{,2}(x * y) for pow(exp{,2}(x), y); ----
1959 /// ldexp(1.0, x) for pow(2.0, itofp(x)); exp2(n * x) for pow(2.0 ** n, x); ----
1960 /// exp10(x) for pow(10.0, x); exp2(log2(n) * x) for pow(n, x). ----
1961 Value *LibCallSimplifier::replacePowWithExp(CallInst *Pow, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
1962 Module *M = Pow->getModule(); 0
1963 Value *Base = Pow->getArgOperand(0), *Expo = Pow->getArgOperand(1); 0
1964 Module *Mod = Pow->getModule(); 0
1965 Type *Ty = Pow->getType(); 0
1966 bool Ignored; ----
1967 ----
1968 // Evaluate special cases related to a nested function as the base. ----
1969 ----
1970 // pow(exp(x), y) -> exp(x * y) ----
1971 // pow(exp2(x), y) -> exp2(x * y) ----
1972 // If exp{,2}() is used only once, it is better to fold two transcendental ----
1973 // math functions into one. If used again, exp{,2}() would still have to be ----
1974 // called with the original argument, then keep both original transcendental ----
1975 // functions. However, this transformation is only safe with fully relaxed ----
1976 // math semantics, since, besides rounding differences, it changes overflow ----
1977 // and underflow behavior quite dramatically. For example: ----
1978 // pow(exp(1000), 0.001) = pow(inf, 0.001) = inf ----
1979 // Whereas: ----
1980 // exp(1000 * 0.001) = exp(1) ----
1981 // TODO: Loosen the requirement for fully relaxed math semantics. ----
1982 // TODO: Handle exp10() when more targets have it available. ----
1983 CallInst *BaseFn = dyn_cast(Base); 0
1984 if (BaseFn && BaseFn->hasOneUse() && BaseFn->isFast() && Pow->isFast()) { 0
1985 LibFunc LibFn; ----
1986 ----
1987 Function *CalleeFn = BaseFn->getCalledFunction(); 0
1988 if (CalleeFn && TLI->getLibFunc(CalleeFn->getName(), LibFn) && 0
1989 isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFn)) { 0
1990 StringRef ExpName; 0
1991 Intrinsic::ID ID; ----
1992 Value *ExpFn; ----
1993 LibFunc LibFnFloat, LibFnDouble, LibFnLongDouble; ----
1994 ----
1995 switch (LibFn) { 0
1996 default: 0
1997 return nullptr; 0
1998 case LibFunc_expf: 0
1999 case LibFunc_exp: ----
2000 case LibFunc_expl: ----
2001 ExpName = TLI->getName(LibFunc_exp); 0
2002 ID = Intrinsic::exp; 0
2003 LibFnFloat = LibFunc_expf; 0
2004 LibFnDouble = LibFunc_exp; 0
2005 LibFnLongDouble = LibFunc_expl; 0
2006 break; 0
2007 case LibFunc_exp2f: 0
2008 case LibFunc_exp2: ----
2009 case LibFunc_exp2l: ----
2010 ExpName = TLI->getName(LibFunc_exp2); 0
2011 ID = Intrinsic::exp2; 0
2012 LibFnFloat = LibFunc_exp2f; 0
2013 LibFnDouble = LibFunc_exp2; 0
2014 LibFnLongDouble = LibFunc_exp2l; 0
2015 break; 0
2016 } ----
2017 ----
2018 // Create new exp{,2}() with the product as its argument. ----
2019 Value *FMul = B.CreateFMul(BaseFn->getArgOperand(0), Expo, "mul"); 0
2020 ExpFn = BaseFn->doesNotAccessMemory() 0
2021 ? B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, ID, Ty), 0
2022 FMul, ExpName) ----
2023 : emitUnaryFloatFnCall(FMul, TLI, LibFnDouble, LibFnFloat, 0
2024 LibFnLongDouble, B, ----
2025 BaseFn->getAttributes()); 0
2026 ----
2027 // Since the new exp{,2}() is different from the original one, dead code ----
2028 // elimination cannot be trusted to remove it, since it may have side ----
2029 // effects (e.g., errno). When the only consumer for the original ----
2030 // exp{,2}() is pow(), then it has to be explicitly erased. ----
2031 substituteInParent(BaseFn, ExpFn); 0
2032 return ExpFn; 0
2033 } ----
2034 } ----
2035 ----
2036 // Evaluate special cases related to a constant base. ----
2037 ----
2038 const APFloat *BaseF; ----
2039 if (!match(Pow->getArgOperand(0), m_APFloat(BaseF))) 0
2040 return nullptr; 0
2041 ----
2042 AttributeList NoAttrs; // Attributes are only meaningful on the original call 0
2043 ----
2044 // pow(2.0, itofp(x)) -> ldexp(1.0, x) ----
2045 // TODO: This does not work for vectors because there is no ldexp intrinsic. ----
2046 if (!Ty->isVectorTy() && match(Base, m_SpecificFP(2.0)) && 0
2047 (isa(Expo) || isa(Expo)) && 0
2048 hasFloatFn(M, TLI, Ty, LibFunc_ldexp, LibFunc_ldexpf, LibFunc_ldexpl)) { 0
2049 if (Value *ExpoI = getIntToFPVal(Expo, B, TLI->getIntSize())) 0
2050 return copyFlags(*Pow, 0
2051 emitBinaryFloatFnCall(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), ExpoI, 0
2052 TLI, LibFunc_ldexp, LibFunc_ldexpf, ----
2053 LibFunc_ldexpl, B, NoAttrs)); 0
2054 } ----
2055 ----
2056 // pow(2.0 ** n, x) -> exp2(n * x) ----
2057 if (hasFloatFn(M, TLI, Ty, LibFunc_exp2, LibFunc_exp2f, LibFunc_exp2l)) { 0
2058 APFloat BaseR = APFloat(1.0); 0
2059 BaseR.convert(BaseF->getSemantics(), APFloat::rmTowardZero, &Ignored); 0
2060 BaseR = BaseR / *BaseF; 0
2061 bool IsInteger = BaseF->isInteger(), IsReciprocal = BaseR.isInteger(); 0
2062 const APFloat *NF = IsReciprocal ? &BaseR : BaseF; 0
2063 APSInt NI(64, false); 0
2064 if ((IsInteger || IsReciprocal) && 0
2065 NF->convertToInteger(NI, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &Ignored) == 0
2066 APFloat::opOK && 0
2067 NI > 1 && NI.isPowerOf2()) { 0
2068 double N = NI.logBase2() * (IsReciprocal ? -1.0 : 1.0); 0
2069 Value *FMul = B.CreateFMul(Expo, ConstantFP::get(Ty, N), "mul"); 0
2070 if (Pow->doesNotAccessMemory()) 0
2071 return copyFlags(*Pow, B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration( 0
2072 Mod, Intrinsic::exp2, Ty), ----
2073 FMul, "exp2")); 0
2074 else ----
2075 return copyFlags(*Pow, emitUnaryFloatFnCall(FMul, TLI, LibFunc_exp2, 0
2076 LibFunc_exp2f, ----
2077 LibFunc_exp2l, B, NoAttrs)); 0
2078 } ----
2079 } 0
2080 ----
2081 // pow(10.0, x) -> exp10(x) ----
2082 // TODO: There is no exp10() intrinsic yet, but some day there shall be one. ----
2083 if (match(Base, m_SpecificFP(10.0)) && 0
2084 hasFloatFn(M, TLI, Ty, LibFunc_exp10, LibFunc_exp10f, LibFunc_exp10l)) 0
2085 return copyFlags(*Pow, emitUnaryFloatFnCall(Expo, TLI, LibFunc_exp10, 0
2086 LibFunc_exp10f, LibFunc_exp10l, ----
2087 B, NoAttrs)); 0
2088 ----
2089 // pow(x, y) -> exp2(log2(x) * y) ----
2090 if (Pow->hasApproxFunc() && Pow->hasNoNaNs() && BaseF->isFiniteNonZero() && 0
2091 !BaseF->isNegative()) { 0
2092 // pow(1, inf) is defined to be 1 but exp2(log2(1) * inf) evaluates to NaN. ----
2093 // Luckily optimizePow has already handled the x == 1 case. ----
2094 assert(!match(Base, m_FPOne()) && 0
2095 "pow(1.0, y) should have been simplified earlier!"); ----
2096 ----
2097 Value *Log = nullptr; 0
2098 if (Ty->isFloatTy()) 0
2099 Log = ConstantFP::get(Ty, std::log2(BaseF->convertToFloat())); 0
2100 else if (Ty->isDoubleTy()) 0
2101 Log = ConstantFP::get(Ty, std::log2(BaseF->convertToDouble())); 0
2102 ----
2103 if (Log) { 0
2104 Value *FMul = B.CreateFMul(Log, Expo, "mul"); 0
2105 if (Pow->doesNotAccessMemory()) 0
2106 return copyFlags(*Pow, B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration( 0
2107 Mod, Intrinsic::exp2, Ty), ----
2108 FMul, "exp2")); 0
2109 else if (hasFloatFn(M, TLI, Ty, LibFunc_exp2, LibFunc_exp2f, 0
2110 LibFunc_exp2l)) ----
2111 return copyFlags(*Pow, emitUnaryFloatFnCall(FMul, TLI, LibFunc_exp2, 0
2112 LibFunc_exp2f, ----
2113 LibFunc_exp2l, B, NoAttrs)); 0
2114 } ----
2115 } ----
2116 ----
2117 return nullptr; 0
2118 } ----
2119 ----
2120 static Value *getSqrtCall(Value *V, AttributeList Attrs, bool NoErrno, 0
2121 Module *M, IRBuilderBase &B, ----
2122 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) { ----
2123 // If errno is never set, then use the intrinsic for sqrt(). ----
2124 if (NoErrno) { 0
2125 Function *SqrtFn = ----
2126 Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::sqrt, V->getType()); 0
2127 return B.CreateCall(SqrtFn, V, "sqrt"); 0
2128 } ----
2129 ----
2130 // Otherwise, use the libcall for sqrt(). ----
2131 if (hasFloatFn(M, TLI, V->getType(), LibFunc_sqrt, LibFunc_sqrtf, 0
2132 LibFunc_sqrtl)) ----
2133 // TODO: We also should check that the target can in fact lower the sqrt() ----
2134 // libcall. We currently have no way to ask this question, so we ask if ----
2135 // the target has a sqrt() libcall, which is not exactly the same. ----
2136 return emitUnaryFloatFnCall(V, TLI, LibFunc_sqrt, LibFunc_sqrtf, 0
2137 LibFunc_sqrtl, B, Attrs); 0
2138 ----
2139 return nullptr; 0
2140 } ----
2141 ----
2142 /// Use square root in place of pow(x, +/-0.5). ----
2143 Value *LibCallSimplifier::replacePowWithSqrt(CallInst *Pow, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2144 Value *Sqrt, *Base = Pow->getArgOperand(0), *Expo = Pow->getArgOperand(1); 0
2145 Module *Mod = Pow->getModule(); 0
2146 Type *Ty = Pow->getType(); 0
2147 ----
2148 const APFloat *ExpoF; ----
2149 if (!match(Expo, m_APFloat(ExpoF)) || 0
2150 (!ExpoF->isExactlyValue(0.5) && !ExpoF->isExactlyValue(-0.5))) 0
2151 return nullptr; 0
2152 ----
2153 // Converting pow(X, -0.5) to 1/sqrt(X) may introduce an extra rounding step, ----
2154 // so that requires fast-math-flags (afn or reassoc). ----
2155 if (ExpoF->isNegative() && (!Pow->hasApproxFunc() && !Pow->hasAllowReassoc())) 0
2156 return nullptr; 0
2157 ----
2158 // If we have a pow() library call (accesses memory) and we can't guarantee ----
2159 // that the base is not an infinity, give up: ----
2160 // pow(-Inf, 0.5) is optionally required to have a result of +Inf (not setting ----
2161 // errno), but sqrt(-Inf) is required by various standards to set errno. ----
2162 if (!Pow->doesNotAccessMemory() && !Pow->hasNoInfs() && 0
2163 !isKnownNeverInfinity(Base, DL, TLI, 0, AC, Pow)) 0
2164 return nullptr; 0
2165 ----
2166 Sqrt = getSqrtCall(Base, AttributeList(), Pow->doesNotAccessMemory(), Mod, B, 0
2167 TLI); ----
2168 if (!Sqrt) 0
2169 return nullptr; 0
2170 ----
2171 // Handle signed zero base by expanding to fabs(sqrt(x)). ----
2172 if (!Pow->hasNoSignedZeros()) { 0
2173 Function *FAbsFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, Intrinsic::fabs, Ty); 0
2174 Sqrt = B.CreateCall(FAbsFn, Sqrt, "abs"); 0
2175 } ----
2176 ----
2177 Sqrt = copyFlags(*Pow, Sqrt); 0
2178 ----
2179 // Handle non finite base by expanding to ----
2180 // (x == -infinity ? +infinity : sqrt(x)). ----
2181 if (!Pow->hasNoInfs()) { 0
2182 Value *PosInf = ConstantFP::getInfinity(Ty), 0
2183 *NegInf = ConstantFP::getInfinity(Ty, true); 0
2184 Value *FCmp = B.CreateFCmpOEQ(Base, NegInf, "isinf"); 0
2185 Sqrt = B.CreateSelect(FCmp, PosInf, Sqrt); 0
2186 } ----
2187 ----
2188 // If the exponent is negative, then get the reciprocal. ----
2189 if (ExpoF->isNegative()) 0
2190 Sqrt = B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), Sqrt, "reciprocal"); 0
2191 ----
2192 return Sqrt; 0
2193 } ----
2194 ----
2195 static Value *createPowWithIntegerExponent(Value *Base, Value *Expo, Module *M, 0
2196 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
2197 Value *Args[] = {Base, Expo}; 0
2198 Type *Types[] = {Base->getType(), Expo->getType()}; 0
2199 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::powi, Types); 0
2200 return B.CreateCall(F, Args); 0
2201 } ----
2202 ----
2203 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePow(CallInst *Pow, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2204 Value *Base = Pow->getArgOperand(0); 0
2205 Value *Expo = Pow->getArgOperand(1); 0
2206 Function *Callee = Pow->getCalledFunction(); 0
2207 StringRef Name = Callee->getName(); 0
2208 Type *Ty = Pow->getType(); 0
2209 Module *M = Pow->getModule(); 0
2210 bool AllowApprox = Pow->hasApproxFunc(); 0
2211 bool Ignored; ----
2212 ----
2213 // Propagate the math semantics from the call to any created instructions. ----
2214 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
2215 B.setFastMathFlags(Pow->getFastMathFlags()); 0
2216 // Evaluate special cases related to the base. ----
2217 ----
2218 // pow(1.0, x) -> 1.0 ----
2219 if (match(Base, m_FPOne())) 0
2220 return Base; 0
2221 ----
2222 if (Value *Exp = replacePowWithExp(Pow, B)) 0
2223 return Exp; 0
2224 ----
2225 // Evaluate special cases related to the exponent. ----
2226 ----
2227 // pow(x, -1.0) -> 1.0 / x ----
2228 if (match(Expo, m_SpecificFP(-1.0))) 0
2229 return B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), Base, "reciprocal"); 0
2230 ----
2231 // pow(x, +/-0.0) -> 1.0 ----
2232 if (match(Expo, m_AnyZeroFP())) 0
2233 return ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0); 0
2234 ----
2235 // pow(x, 1.0) -> x ----
2236 if (match(Expo, m_FPOne())) 0
2237 return Base; 0
2238 ----
2239 // pow(x, 2.0) -> x * x ----
2240 if (match(Expo, m_SpecificFP(2.0))) 0
2241 return B.CreateFMul(Base, Base, "square"); 0
2242 ----
2243 if (Value *Sqrt = replacePowWithSqrt(Pow, B)) 0
2244 return Sqrt; 0
2245 ----
2246 // If we can approximate pow: ----
2247 // pow(x, n) -> powi(x, n) * sqrt(x) if n has exactly a 0.5 fraction ----
2248 // pow(x, n) -> powi(x, n) if n is a constant signed integer value ----
2249 const APFloat *ExpoF; ----
2250 if (AllowApprox && match(Expo, m_APFloat(ExpoF)) && 0
2251 !ExpoF->isExactlyValue(0.5) && !ExpoF->isExactlyValue(-0.5)) { 0
2252 APFloat ExpoA(abs(*ExpoF)); 0
2253 APFloat ExpoI(*ExpoF); 0
2254 Value *Sqrt = nullptr; 0
2255 if (!ExpoA.isInteger()) { 0
2256 APFloat Expo2 = ExpoA; 0
2257 // To check if ExpoA is an integer + 0.5, we add it to itself. If there ----
2258 // is no floating point exception and the result is an integer, then ----
2259 // ExpoA == integer + 0.5 ----
2260 if (Expo2.add(ExpoA, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven) != APFloat::opOK) 0
2261 return nullptr; 0
2262 ----
2263 if (!Expo2.isInteger()) 0
2264 return nullptr; 0
2265 ----
2266 if (ExpoI.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardNegative) != 0
2267 APFloat::opInexact) ----
2268 return nullptr; 0
2269 if (!ExpoI.isInteger()) 0
2270 return nullptr; 0
2271 ExpoF = &ExpoI; 0
2272 ----
2273 Sqrt = getSqrtCall(Base, AttributeList(), Pow->doesNotAccessMemory(), M, 0
2274 B, TLI); ----
2275 if (!Sqrt) 0
2276 return nullptr; 0
2277 } 0
2278 ----
2279 // 0.5 fraction is now optionally handled. ----
2280 // Do pow -> powi for remaining integer exponent ----
2281 APSInt IntExpo(TLI->getIntSize(), /*isUnsigned=*/false); 0
2282 if (ExpoF->isInteger() && 0
2283 ExpoF->convertToInteger(IntExpo, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &Ignored) == 0
2284 APFloat::opOK) { ----
2285 Value *PowI = copyFlags( 0
2286 *Pow, ----
2287 createPowWithIntegerExponent( ----
2288 Base, ConstantInt::get(B.getIntNTy(TLI->getIntSize()), IntExpo), 0
2289 M, B)); ----
2290 ----
2291 if (PowI && Sqrt) 0
2292 return B.CreateFMul(PowI, Sqrt); 0
2293 ----
2294 return PowI; 0
2295 } ----
2296 } 0
2297 ----
2298 // powf(x, itofp(y)) -> powi(x, y) ----
2299 if (AllowApprox && (isa(Expo) || isa(Expo))) { 0
2300 if (Value *ExpoI = getIntToFPVal(Expo, B, TLI->getIntSize())) 0
2301 return copyFlags(*Pow, createPowWithIntegerExponent(Base, ExpoI, M, B)); 0
2302 } ----
2303 ----
2304 // Shrink pow() to powf() if the arguments are single precision, ----
2305 // unless the result is expected to be double precision. ----
2306 if (UnsafeFPShrink && Name == TLI->getName(LibFunc_pow) && 0
2307 hasFloatVersion(M, Name)) { 0
2308 if (Value *Shrunk = optimizeBinaryDoubleFP(Pow, B, TLI, true)) 0
2309 return Shrunk; 0
2310 } ----
2311 ----
2312 return nullptr; 0
2313 } 0
2314 ----
2315 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeExp2(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2316 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
2317 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
2318 StringRef Name = Callee->getName(); 0
2319 Value *Ret = nullptr; 0
2320 if (UnsafeFPShrink && Name == TLI->getName(LibFunc_exp2) && 0
2321 hasFloatVersion(M, Name)) 0
2322 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, TLI, true); 0
2323 ----
2324 // Bail out for vectors because the code below only expects scalars. ----
2325 // TODO: This could be allowed if we had a ldexp intrinsic (D14327). ----
2326 Type *Ty = CI->getType(); 0
2327 if (Ty->isVectorTy()) 0
2328 return Ret; 0
2329 ----
2330 // exp2(sitofp(x)) -> ldexp(1.0, sext(x)) if sizeof(x) <= IntSize ----
2331 // exp2(uitofp(x)) -> ldexp(1.0, zext(x)) if sizeof(x) < IntSize ----
2332 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2333 if ((isa(Op) || isa(Op)) && 0
2334 hasFloatFn(M, TLI, Ty, LibFunc_ldexp, LibFunc_ldexpf, LibFunc_ldexpl)) { 0
2335 if (Value *Exp = getIntToFPVal(Op, B, TLI->getIntSize())) { 0
2336 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
2337 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags()); 0
2338 return copyFlags( 0
2339 *CI, emitBinaryFloatFnCall(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), Exp, TLI, 0
2340 LibFunc_ldexp, LibFunc_ldexpf, ----
2341 LibFunc_ldexpl, B, AttributeList())); 0
2342 } 0
2343 } ----
2344 ----
2345 return Ret; 0
2346 } ----
2347 ----
2348 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFMinFMax(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2349 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
2350 ----
2351 // If we can shrink the call to a float function rather than a double ----
2352 // function, do that first. ----
2353 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
2354 StringRef Name = Callee->getName(); 0
2355 if ((Name == "fmin" || Name == "fmax") && hasFloatVersion(M, Name)) 0
2356 if (Value *Ret = optimizeBinaryDoubleFP(CI, B, TLI)) 0
2357 return Ret; 0
2358 ----
2359 // The LLVM intrinsics minnum/maxnum correspond to fmin/fmax. Canonicalize to ----
2360 // the intrinsics for improved optimization (for example, vectorization). ----
2361 // No-signed-zeros is implied by the definitions of fmax/fmin themselves. ----
2362 // From the C standard draft WG14/N1256: ----
2363 // "Ideally, fmax would be sensitive to the sign of zero, for example ----
2364 // fmax(-0.0, +0.0) would return +0; however, implementation in software ----
2365 // might be impractical." ----
2366 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
2367 FastMathFlags FMF = CI->getFastMathFlags(); 0
2368 FMF.setNoSignedZeros(); 0
2369 B.setFastMathFlags(FMF); 0
2370 ----
2371 Intrinsic::ID IID = Callee->getName().startswith("fmin") ? Intrinsic::minnum 0
2372 : Intrinsic::maxnum; 0
2373 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getModule(), IID, CI->getType()); 0
2374 return copyFlags( 0
2375 *CI, B.CreateCall(F, {CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1)})); 0
2376 } 0
2377 ----
2378 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeLog(CallInst *Log, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2379 Function *LogFn = Log->getCalledFunction(); 0
2380 StringRef LogNm = LogFn->getName(); 0
2381 Intrinsic::ID LogID = LogFn->getIntrinsicID(); 0
2382 Module *Mod = Log->getModule(); 0
2383 Type *Ty = Log->getType(); 0
2384 Value *Ret = nullptr; 0
2385 ----
2386 if (UnsafeFPShrink && hasFloatVersion(Mod, LogNm)) 0
2387 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(Log, B, TLI, true); 0
2388 ----
2389 // The earlier call must also be 'fast' in order to do these transforms. ----
2390 CallInst *Arg = dyn_cast(Log->getArgOperand(0)); 0
2391 if (!Log->isFast() || !Arg || !Arg->isFast() || !Arg->hasOneUse()) 0
2392 return Ret; 0
2393 ----
2394 LibFunc LogLb, ExpLb, Exp2Lb, Exp10Lb, PowLb; ----
2395 ----
2396 // This is only applicable to log(), log2(), log10(). ----
2397 if (TLI->getLibFunc(LogNm, LogLb)) 0
2398 switch (LogLb) { 0
2399 case LibFunc_logf: 0
2400 LogID = Intrinsic::log; 0
2401 ExpLb = LibFunc_expf; 0
2402 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2f; 0
2403 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10f; 0
2404 PowLb = LibFunc_powf; 0
2405 break; 0
2406 case LibFunc_log: 0
2407 LogID = Intrinsic::log; 0
2408 ExpLb = LibFunc_exp; 0
2409 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2; 0
2410 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10; 0
2411 PowLb = LibFunc_pow; 0
2412 break; 0
2413 case LibFunc_logl: 0
2414 LogID = Intrinsic::log; 0
2415 ExpLb = LibFunc_expl; 0
2416 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2l; 0
2417 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10l; 0
2418 PowLb = LibFunc_powl; 0
2419 break; 0
2420 case LibFunc_log2f: 0
2421 LogID = Intrinsic::log2; 0
2422 ExpLb = LibFunc_expf; 0
2423 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2f; 0
2424 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10f; 0
2425 PowLb = LibFunc_powf; 0
2426 break; 0
2427 case LibFunc_log2: 0
2428 LogID = Intrinsic::log2; 0
2429 ExpLb = LibFunc_exp; 0
2430 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2; 0
2431 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10; 0
2432 PowLb = LibFunc_pow; 0
2433 break; 0
2434 case LibFunc_log2l: 0
2435 LogID = Intrinsic::log2; 0
2436 ExpLb = LibFunc_expl; 0
2437 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2l; 0
2438 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10l; 0
2439 PowLb = LibFunc_powl; 0
2440 break; 0
2441 case LibFunc_log10f: 0
2442 LogID = Intrinsic::log10; 0
2443 ExpLb = LibFunc_expf; 0
2444 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2f; 0
2445 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10f; 0
2446 PowLb = LibFunc_powf; 0
2447 break; 0
2448 case LibFunc_log10: 0
2449 LogID = Intrinsic::log10; 0
2450 ExpLb = LibFunc_exp; 0
2451 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2; 0
2452 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10; 0
2453 PowLb = LibFunc_pow; 0
2454 break; 0
2455 case LibFunc_log10l: 0
2456 LogID = Intrinsic::log10; 0
2457 ExpLb = LibFunc_expl; 0
2458 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2l; 0
2459 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10l; 0
2460 PowLb = LibFunc_powl; 0
2461 break; 0
2462 default: 0
2463 return Ret; 0
2464 } ----
2465 else if (LogID == Intrinsic::log || LogID == Intrinsic::log2 || 0
2466 LogID == Intrinsic::log10) { ----
2467 if (Ty->getScalarType()->isFloatTy()) { 0
2468 ExpLb = LibFunc_expf; 0
2469 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2f; 0
2470 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10f; 0
2471 PowLb = LibFunc_powf; 0
2472 } else if (Ty->getScalarType()->isDoubleTy()) { 0
2473 ExpLb = LibFunc_exp; 0
2474 Exp2Lb = LibFunc_exp2; 0
2475 Exp10Lb = LibFunc_exp10; 0
2476 PowLb = LibFunc_pow; 0
2477 } else ----
2478 return Ret; 0
2479 } else ----
2480 return Ret; 0
2481 ----
2482 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
2483 B.setFastMathFlags(FastMathFlags::getFast()); 0
2484 ----
2485 Intrinsic::ID ArgID = Arg->getIntrinsicID(); 0
2486 LibFunc ArgLb = NotLibFunc; 0
2487 TLI->getLibFunc(*Arg, ArgLb); 0
2488 ----
2489 // log(pow(x,y)) -> y*log(x) ----
2490 AttributeList NoAttrs; 0
2491 if (ArgLb == PowLb || ArgID == Intrinsic::pow) { 0
2492 Value *LogX = ----
2493 Log->doesNotAccessMemory() 0
2494 ? B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, LogID, Ty), 0
2495 Arg->getOperand(0), "log") 0
2496 : emitUnaryFloatFnCall(Arg->getOperand(0), TLI, LogNm, B, NoAttrs); 0
2497 Value *MulY = B.CreateFMul(Arg->getArgOperand(1), LogX, "mul"); 0
2498 // Since pow() may have side effects, e.g. errno, ----
2499 // dead code elimination may not be trusted to remove it. ----
2500 substituteInParent(Arg, MulY); 0
2501 return MulY; 0
2502 } ----
2503 ----
2504 // log(exp{,2,10}(y)) -> y*log({e,2,10}) ----
2505 // TODO: There is no exp10() intrinsic yet. ----
2506 if (ArgLb == ExpLb || ArgLb == Exp2Lb || ArgLb == Exp10Lb || 0
2507 ArgID == Intrinsic::exp || ArgID == Intrinsic::exp2) { 0
2508 Constant *Eul; ----
2509 if (ArgLb == ExpLb || ArgID == Intrinsic::exp) 0
2510 // FIXME: Add more precise value of e for long double. ----
2511 Eul = ConstantFP::get(Log->getType(), numbers::e); 0
2512 else if (ArgLb == Exp2Lb || ArgID == Intrinsic::exp2) 0
2513 Eul = ConstantFP::get(Log->getType(), 2.0); 0
2514 else ----
2515 Eul = ConstantFP::get(Log->getType(), 10.0); 0
2516 Value *LogE = Log->doesNotAccessMemory() 0
2517 ? B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, LogID, Ty), 0
2518 Eul, "log") 0
2519 : emitUnaryFloatFnCall(Eul, TLI, LogNm, B, NoAttrs); 0
2520 Value *MulY = B.CreateFMul(Arg->getArgOperand(0), LogE, "mul"); 0
2521 // Since exp() may have side effects, e.g. errno, ----
2522 // dead code elimination may not be trusted to remove it. ----
2523 substituteInParent(Arg, MulY); 0
2524 return MulY; 0
2525 } ----
2526 ----
2527 return Ret; 0
2528 } ----
2529 ----
2530 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSqrt(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2531 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
2532 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
2533 Value *Ret = nullptr; 0
2534 // TODO: Once we have a way (other than checking for the existince of the ----
2535 // libcall) to tell whether our target can lower @llvm.sqrt, relax the ----
2536 // condition below. ----
2537 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_sqrtf) && 0
2538 (Callee->getName() == "sqrt" || 0
2539 Callee->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::sqrt)) 0
2540 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, TLI, true); 0
2541 ----
2542 if (!CI->isFast()) 0
2543 return Ret; 0
2544 ----
2545 Instruction *I = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(0)); 0
2546 if (!I || I->getOpcode() != Instruction::FMul || !I->isFast()) 0
2547 return Ret; 0
2548 ----
2549 // We're looking for a repeated factor in a multiplication tree, ----
2550 // so we can do this fold: sqrt(x * x) -> fabs(x); ----
2551 // or this fold: sqrt((x * x) * y) -> fabs(x) * sqrt(y). ----
2552 Value *Op0 = I->getOperand(0); 0
2553 Value *Op1 = I->getOperand(1); 0
2554 Value *RepeatOp = nullptr; 0
2555 Value *OtherOp = nullptr; 0
2556 if (Op0 == Op1) { 0
2557 // Simple match: the operands of the multiply are identical. ----
2558 RepeatOp = Op0; 0
2559 } else { ----
2560 // Look for a more complicated pattern: one of the operands is itself ----
2561 // a multiply, so search for a common factor in that multiply. ----
2562 // Note: We don't bother looking any deeper than this first level or for ----
2563 // variations of this pattern because instcombine's visitFMUL and/or the ----
2564 // reassociation pass should give us this form. ----
2565 Value *OtherMul0, *OtherMul1; ----
2566 if (match(Op0, m_FMul(m_Value(OtherMul0), m_Value(OtherMul1)))) { 0
2567 // Pattern: sqrt((x * y) * z) ----
2568 if (OtherMul0 == OtherMul1 && cast(Op0)->isFast()) { 0
2569 // Matched: sqrt((x * x) * z) ----
2570 RepeatOp = OtherMul0; 0
2571 OtherOp = Op1; 0
2572 } ----
2573 } ----
2574 } ----
2575 if (!RepeatOp) 0
2576 return Ret; 0
2577 ----
2578 // Fast math flags for any created instructions should match the sqrt ----
2579 // and multiply. ----
2580 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B); 0
2581 B.setFastMathFlags(I->getFastMathFlags()); 0
2582 ----
2583 // If we found a repeated factor, hoist it out of the square root and ----
2584 // replace it with the fabs of that factor. ----
2585 Type *ArgType = I->getType(); 0
2586 Function *Fabs = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::fabs, ArgType); 0
2587 Value *FabsCall = B.CreateCall(Fabs, RepeatOp, "fabs"); 0
2588 if (OtherOp) { 0
2589 // If we found a non-repeated factor, we still need to get its square ----
2590 // root. We then multiply that by the value that was simplified out ----
2591 // of the square root calculation. ----
2592 Function *Sqrt = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::sqrt, ArgType); 0
2593 Value *SqrtCall = B.CreateCall(Sqrt, OtherOp, "sqrt"); 0
2594 return copyFlags(*CI, B.CreateFMul(FabsCall, SqrtCall)); 0
2595 } ----
2596 return copyFlags(*CI, FabsCall); 0
2597 } 0
2598 ----
2599 // TODO: Generalize to handle any trig function and its inverse. ----
2600 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeTan(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2601 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
2602 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
2603 Value *Ret = nullptr; 0
2604 StringRef Name = Callee->getName(); 0
2605 if (UnsafeFPShrink && Name == "tan" && hasFloatVersion(M, Name)) 0
2606 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, TLI, true); 0
2607 ----
2608 Value *Op1 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2609 auto *OpC = dyn_cast(Op1); 0
2610 if (!OpC) 0
2611 return Ret; 0
2612 ----
2613 // Both calls must be 'fast' in order to remove them. ----
2614 if (!CI->isFast() || !OpC->isFast()) 0
2615 return Ret; 0
2616 ----
2617 // tan(atan(x)) -> x ----
2618 // tanf(atanf(x)) -> x ----
2619 // tanl(atanl(x)) -> x ----
2620 LibFunc Func; ----
2621 Function *F = OpC->getCalledFunction(); 0
2622 if (F && TLI->getLibFunc(F->getName(), Func) && 0
2623 isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, Func) && 0
2624 ((Func == LibFunc_atan && Callee->getName() == "tan") || 0
2625 (Func == LibFunc_atanf && Callee->getName() == "tanf") || 0
2626 (Func == LibFunc_atanl && Callee->getName() == "tanl"))) 0
2627 Ret = OpC->getArgOperand(0); 0
2628 return Ret; 0
2629 } ----
2630 ----
2631 static bool isTrigLibCall(CallInst *CI) { 0
2632 // We can only hope to do anything useful if we can ignore things like errno ----
2633 // and floating-point exceptions. ----
2634 // We already checked the prototype. ----
2635 return CI->doesNotThrow() && CI->doesNotAccessMemory(); 0
2636 } ----
2637 ----
2638 static bool insertSinCosCall(IRBuilderBase &B, Function *OrigCallee, Value *Arg, 0
2639 bool UseFloat, Value *&Sin, Value *&Cos, ----
2640 Value *&SinCos, const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) { ----
2641 Module *M = OrigCallee->getParent(); 0
2642 Type *ArgTy = Arg->getType(); 0
2643 Type *ResTy; ----
2644 StringRef Name; 0
2645 ----
2646 Triple T(OrigCallee->getParent()->getTargetTriple()); 0
2647 if (UseFloat) { 0
2648 Name = "__sincospif_stret"; 0
2649 ----
2650 assert(T.getArch() != Triple::x86 && "x86 messy and unsupported for now"); 0
2651 // x86_64 can't use {float, float} since that would be returned in both ----
2652 // xmm0 and xmm1, which isn't what a real struct would do. ----
2653 ResTy = T.getArch() == Triple::x86_64 0
2654 ? static_cast(FixedVectorType::get(ArgTy, 2)) 0
2655 : static_cast(StructType::get(ArgTy, ArgTy)); 0
2656 } else { ----
2657 Name = "__sincospi_stret"; 0
2658 ResTy = StructType::get(ArgTy, ArgTy); 0
2659 } ----
2660 ----
2661 if (!isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, Name)) 0
2662 return false; 0
2663 LibFunc TheLibFunc; ----
2664 TLI->getLibFunc(Name, TheLibFunc); 0
2665 FunctionCallee Callee = getOrInsertLibFunc( 0
2666 M, *TLI, TheLibFunc, OrigCallee->getAttributes(), ResTy, ArgTy); ----
2667 ----
2668 if (Instruction *ArgInst = dyn_cast(Arg)) { 0
2669 // If the argument is an instruction, it must dominate all uses so put our ----
2670 // sincos call there. ----
2671 B.SetInsertPoint(ArgInst->getParent(), ++ArgInst->getIterator()); 0
2672 } else { ----
2673 // Otherwise (e.g. for a constant) the beginning of the function is as ----
2674 // good a place as any. ----
2675 BasicBlock &EntryBB = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getEntryBlock(); 0
2676 B.SetInsertPoint(&EntryBB, EntryBB.begin()); 0
2677 } ----
2678 ----
2679 SinCos = B.CreateCall(Callee, Arg, "sincospi"); 0
2680 ----
2681 if (SinCos->getType()->isStructTy()) { 0
2682 Sin = B.CreateExtractValue(SinCos, 0, "sinpi"); 0
2683 Cos = B.CreateExtractValue(SinCos, 1, "cospi"); 0
2684 } else { ----
2685 Sin = B.CreateExtractElement(SinCos, ConstantInt::get(B.getInt32Ty(), 0), 0
2686 "sinpi"); ----
2687 Cos = B.CreateExtractElement(SinCos, ConstantInt::get(B.getInt32Ty(), 1), 0
2688 "cospi"); ----
2689 } ----
2690 ----
2691 return true; 0
2692 } 0
2693 ----
2694 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSinCosPi(CallInst *CI, bool IsSin, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2695 // Make sure the prototype is as expected, otherwise the rest of the ----
2696 // function is probably invalid and likely to abort. ----
2697 if (!isTrigLibCall(CI)) 0
2698 return nullptr; 0
2699 ----
2700 Value *Arg = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2701 SmallVector SinCalls; 0
2702 SmallVector CosCalls; 0
2703 SmallVector SinCosCalls; 0
2704 ----
2705 bool IsFloat = Arg->getType()->isFloatTy(); 0
2706 ----
2707 // Look for all compatible sinpi, cospi and sincospi calls with the same ----
2708 // argument. If there are enough (in some sense) we can make the ----
2709 // substitution. ----
2710 Function *F = CI->getFunction(); 0
2711 for (User *U : Arg->users()) 0
2712 classifyArgUse(U, F, IsFloat, SinCalls, CosCalls, SinCosCalls); 0
2713 ----
2714 // It's only worthwhile if both sinpi and cospi are actually used. ----
2715 if (SinCalls.empty() || CosCalls.empty()) 0
2716 return nullptr; 0
2717 ----
2718 Value *Sin, *Cos, *SinCos; ----
2719 if (!insertSinCosCall(B, CI->getCalledFunction(), Arg, IsFloat, Sin, Cos, 0
2720 SinCos, TLI)) ----
2721 return nullptr; 0
2722 ----
2723 auto replaceTrigInsts = [this](SmallVectorImpl &Calls, 0
2724 Value *Res) { 0
2725 for (CallInst *C : Calls) 0
2726 replaceAllUsesWith(C, Res); 0
2727 }; 0
2728 ----
2729 replaceTrigInsts(SinCalls, Sin); 0
2730 replaceTrigInsts(CosCalls, Cos); 0
2731 replaceTrigInsts(SinCosCalls, SinCos); 0
2732 ----
2733 return IsSin ? Sin : Cos; 0
2734 } 0
2735 ----
2736 void LibCallSimplifier::classifyArgUse( 0
2737 Value *Val, Function *F, bool IsFloat, ----
2738 SmallVectorImpl &SinCalls, ----
2739 SmallVectorImpl &CosCalls, ----
2740 SmallVectorImpl &SinCosCalls) { ----
2741 auto *CI = dyn_cast(Val); 0
2742 if (!CI || CI->use_empty()) 0
2743 return; 0
2744 ----
2745 // Don't consider calls in other functions. ----
2746 if (CI->getFunction() != F) 0
2747 return; 0
2748 ----
2749 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
2750 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
2751 LibFunc Func; ----
2752 if (!Callee || !TLI->getLibFunc(*Callee, Func) || 0
2753 !isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, Func) || 0
2754 !isTrigLibCall(CI)) 0
2755 return; 0
2756 ----
2757 if (IsFloat) { 0
2758 if (Func == LibFunc_sinpif) 0
2759 SinCalls.push_back(CI); 0
2760 else if (Func == LibFunc_cospif) 0
2761 CosCalls.push_back(CI); 0
2762 else if (Func == LibFunc_sincospif_stret) 0
2763 SinCosCalls.push_back(CI); 0
2764 } else { ----
2765 if (Func == LibFunc_sinpi) 0
2766 SinCalls.push_back(CI); 0
2767 else if (Func == LibFunc_cospi) 0
2768 CosCalls.push_back(CI); 0
2769 else if (Func == LibFunc_sincospi_stret) 0
2770 SinCosCalls.push_back(CI); 0
2771 } ----
2772 } ----
2773 ----
2774 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2775 // Integer Library Call Optimizations ----
2776 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2777 ----
2778 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFFS(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2779 // All variants of ffs return int which need not be 32 bits wide. ----
2780 // ffs{,l,ll}(x) -> x != 0 ? (int)llvm.cttz(x)+1 : 0 ----
2781 Type *RetType = CI->getType(); 0
2782 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2783 Type *ArgType = Op->getType(); 0
2784 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getCalledFunction()->getParent(), 0
2785 Intrinsic::cttz, ArgType); ----
2786 Value *V = B.CreateCall(F, {Op, B.getTrue()}, "cttz"); 0
2787 V = B.CreateAdd(V, ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), 1)); 0
2788 V = B.CreateIntCast(V, RetType, false); 0
2789 ----
2790 Value *Cond = B.CreateICmpNE(Op, Constant::getNullValue(ArgType)); 0
2791 return B.CreateSelect(Cond, V, ConstantInt::get(RetType, 0)); 0
2792 } ----
2793 ----
2794 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFls(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2795 // All variants of fls return int which need not be 32 bits wide. ----
2796 // fls{,l,ll}(x) -> (int)(sizeInBits(x) - llvm.ctlz(x, false)) ----
2797 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2798 Type *ArgType = Op->getType(); 0
2799 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getCalledFunction()->getParent(), 0
2800 Intrinsic::ctlz, ArgType); ----
2801 Value *V = B.CreateCall(F, {Op, B.getFalse()}, "ctlz"); 0
2802 V = B.CreateSub(ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), ArgType->getIntegerBitWidth()), 0
2803 V); ----
2804 return B.CreateIntCast(V, CI->getType(), false); 0
2805 } ----
2806 ----
2807 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeAbs(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2808 // abs(x) -> x ----
2809 // The negation has 'nsw' because abs of INT_MIN is undefined. ----
2810 Value *X = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2811 Value *IsNeg = B.CreateIsNeg(X); 0
2812 Value *NegX = B.CreateNSWNeg(X, "neg"); 0
2813 return B.CreateSelect(IsNeg, NegX, X); 0
2814 } ----
2815 ----
2816 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeIsDigit(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2817 // isdigit(c) -> (c-'0') ----
2818 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2819 Type *ArgType = Op->getType(); 0
2820 Op = B.CreateSub(Op, ConstantInt::get(ArgType, '0'), "isdigittmp"); 0
2821 Op = B.CreateICmpULT(Op, ConstantInt::get(ArgType, 10), "isdigit"); 0
2822 return B.CreateZExt(Op, CI->getType()); 0
2823 } ----
2824 ----
2825 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeIsAscii(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2826 // isascii(c) -> c ----
2827 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
2828 Type *ArgType = Op->getType(); 0
2829 Op = B.CreateICmpULT(Op, ConstantInt::get(ArgType, 128), "isascii"); 0
2830 return B.CreateZExt(Op, CI->getType()); 0
2831 } ----
2832 ----
2833 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeToAscii(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2834 // toascii(c) -> c & 0x7f ----
2835 return B.CreateAnd(CI->getArgOperand(0), 0
2836 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0x7F)); 0
2837 } ----
2838 ----
2839 // Fold calls to atoi, atol, and atoll. ----
2840 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeAtoi(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2841 CI->addParamAttr(0, Attribute::NoCapture); 0
2842 ----
2843 StringRef Str; 0
2844 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), Str)) 0
2845 return nullptr; 0
2846 ----
2847 return convertStrToInt(CI, Str, nullptr, 10, /*AsSigned=*/true, B); 0
2848 } ----
2849 ----
2850 // Fold calls to strtol, strtoll, strtoul, and strtoull. ----
2851 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrToInt(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
2852 bool AsSigned) { ----
2853 Value *EndPtr = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
2854 if (isa(EndPtr)) { 0
2855 // With a null EndPtr, this function won't capture the main argument. ----
2856 // It would be readonly too, except that it still may write to errno. ----
2857 CI->addParamAttr(0, Attribute::NoCapture); 0
2858 EndPtr = nullptr; 0
2859 } else if (!isKnownNonZero(EndPtr, DL)) 0
2860 return nullptr; 0
2861 ----
2862 StringRef Str; 0
2863 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), Str)) 0
2864 return nullptr; 0
2865 ----
2866 if (ConstantInt *CInt = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(2))) { 0
2867 return convertStrToInt(CI, Str, EndPtr, CInt->getSExtValue(), AsSigned, B); 0
2868 } ----
2869 ----
2870 return nullptr; 0
2871 } ----
2872 ----
2873 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2874 // Formatting and IO Library Call Optimizations ----
2875 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2876 ----
2877 static bool isReportingError(Function *Callee, CallInst *CI, int StreamArg); ----
2878 ----
2879 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeErrorReporting(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B, 0
2880 int StreamArg) { ----
2881 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
2882 // Error reporting calls should be cold, mark them as such. ----
2883 // This applies even to non-builtin calls: it is only a hint and applies to ----
2884 // functions that the frontend might not understand as builtins. ----
2885 ----
2886 // This heuristic was suggested in: ----
2887 // Improving Static Branch Prediction in a Compiler ----
2888 // Brian L. Deitrich, Ben-Chung Cheng, Wen-mei W. Hwu ----
2889 // Proceedings of PACT'98, Oct. 1998, IEEE ----
2890 if (!CI->hasFnAttr(Attribute::Cold) && 0
2891 isReportingError(Callee, CI, StreamArg)) { 0
2892 CI->addFnAttr(Attribute::Cold); 0
2893 } ----
2894 ----
2895 return nullptr; 0
2896 } ----
2897 ----
2898 static bool isReportingError(Function *Callee, CallInst *CI, int StreamArg) { 0
2899 if (!Callee || !Callee->isDeclaration()) 0
2900 return false; 0
2901 ----
2902 if (StreamArg < 0) 0
2903 return true; 0
2904 ----
2905 // These functions might be considered cold, but only if their stream ----
2906 // argument is stderr. ----
2907 ----
2908 if (StreamArg >= (int)CI->arg_size()) 0
2909 return false; 0
2910 LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(StreamArg)); 0
2911 if (!LI) 0
2912 return false; 0
2913 GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(LI->getPointerOperand()); 0
2914 if (!GV || !GV->isDeclaration()) 0
2915 return false; 0
2916 return GV->getName() == "stderr"; 0
2917 } ----
2918 ----
2919 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePrintFString(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2920 // Check for a fixed format string. ----
2921 StringRef FormatStr; 0
2922 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), FormatStr)) 0
2923 return nullptr; 0
2924 ----
2925 // Empty format string -> noop. ----
2926 if (FormatStr.empty()) // Tolerate printf's declared void. 0
2927 return CI->use_empty() ? (Value *)CI : ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
2928 ----
2929 // Do not do any of the following transformations if the printf return value ----
2930 // is used, in general the printf return value is not compatible with either ----
2931 // putchar() or puts(). ----
2932 if (!CI->use_empty()) 0
2933 return nullptr; 0
2934 ----
2935 Type *IntTy = CI->getType(); 0
2936 // printf("x") -> putchar('x'), even for "%" and "%%". ----
2937 if (FormatStr.size() == 1 || FormatStr == "%%") { 0
2938 // Convert the character to unsigned char before passing it to putchar ----
2939 // to avoid host-specific sign extension in the IR. Putchar converts ----
2940 // it to unsigned char regardless. ----
2941 Value *IntChar = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, (unsigned char)FormatStr[0]); 0
2942 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutChar(IntChar, B, TLI)); 0
2943 } ----
2944 ----
2945 // Try to remove call or emit putchar/puts. ----
2946 if (FormatStr == "%s" && CI->arg_size() > 1) { 0
2947 StringRef OperandStr; 0
2948 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getOperand(1), OperandStr)) 0
2949 return nullptr; 0
2950 // printf("%s", "") --> NOP ----
2951 if (OperandStr.empty()) 0
2952 return (Value *)CI; 0
2953 // printf("%s", "a") --> putchar('a') ----
2954 if (OperandStr.size() == 1) { 0
2955 // Convert the character to unsigned char before passing it to putchar ----
2956 // to avoid host-specific sign extension in the IR. Putchar converts ----
2957 // it to unsigned char regardless. ----
2958 Value *IntChar = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, (unsigned char)OperandStr[0]); 0
2959 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutChar(IntChar, B, TLI)); 0
2960 } ----
2961 // printf("%s", str"\n") --> puts(str) ----
2962 if (OperandStr.back() == '\n') { 0
2963 OperandStr = OperandStr.drop_back(); 0
2964 Value *GV = B.CreateGlobalString(OperandStr, "str"); 0
2965 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutS(GV, B, TLI)); 0
2966 } ----
2967 return nullptr; 0
2968 } ----
2969 ----
2970 // printf("foo\n") --> puts("foo") ----
2971 if (FormatStr.back() == '\n' && 0
2972 !FormatStr.contains('%')) { // No format characters. 0
2973 // Create a string literal with no \n on it. We expect the constant merge ----
2974 // pass to be run after this pass, to merge duplicate strings. ----
2975 FormatStr = FormatStr.drop_back(); 0
2976 Value *GV = B.CreateGlobalString(FormatStr, "str"); 0
2977 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutS(GV, B, TLI)); 0
2978 } ----
2979 ----
2980 // Optimize specific format strings. ----
2981 // printf("%c", chr) --> putchar(chr) ----
2982 if (FormatStr == "%c" && CI->arg_size() > 1 && 0
2983 CI->getArgOperand(1)->getType()->isIntegerTy()) { 0
2984 // Convert the argument to the type expected by putchar, i.e., int, which ----
2985 // need not be 32 bits wide but which is the same as printf's return type. ----
2986 Value *IntChar = B.CreateIntCast(CI->getArgOperand(1), IntTy, false); 0
2987 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutChar(IntChar, B, TLI)); 0
2988 } ----
2989 ----
2990 // printf("%s\n", str) --> puts(str) ----
2991 if (FormatStr == "%s\n" && CI->arg_size() > 1 && 0
2992 CI->getArgOperand(1)->getType()->isPointerTy()) 0
2993 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutS(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, TLI)); 0
2994 return nullptr; 0
2995 } ----
2996 ----
2997 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
2998 ----
2999 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
3000 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
3001 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType(); 0
3002 if (Value *V = optimizePrintFString(CI, B)) { 0
3003 return V; 0
3004 } ----
3005 ----
3006 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
3007 ----
3008 // printf(format, ...) -> iprintf(format, ...) if no floating point ----
3009 // arguments. ----
3010 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_iprintf) && 0
3011 !callHasFloatingPointArgument(CI)) { 0
3012 FunctionCallee IPrintFFn = getOrInsertLibFunc(M, *TLI, LibFunc_iprintf, FT, 0
3013 Callee->getAttributes()); ----
3014 CallInst *New = cast(CI->clone()); 0
3015 New->setCalledFunction(IPrintFFn); 0
3016 B.Insert(New); 0
3017 return New; 0
3018 } ----
3019 ----
3020 // printf(format, ...) -> __small_printf(format, ...) if no 128-bit floating point ----
3021 // arguments. ----
3022 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_small_printf) && 0
3023 !callHasFP128Argument(CI)) { 0
3024 auto SmallPrintFFn = getOrInsertLibFunc(M, *TLI, LibFunc_small_printf, FT, 0
3025 Callee->getAttributes()); ----
3026 CallInst *New = cast(CI->clone()); 0
3027 New->setCalledFunction(SmallPrintFFn); 0
3028 B.Insert(New); 0
3029 return New; 0
3030 } ----
3031 ----
3032 return nullptr; 0
3033 } ----
3034 ----
3035 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSPrintFString(CallInst *CI, 0
3036 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
3037 // Check for a fixed format string. ----
3038 StringRef FormatStr; 0
3039 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), FormatStr)) 0
3040 return nullptr; 0
3041 ----
3042 // If we just have a format string (nothing else crazy) transform it. ----
3043 Value *Dest = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
3044 if (CI->arg_size() == 2) { 0
3045 // Make sure there's no % in the constant array. We could try to handle ----
3046 // %% -> % in the future if we cared. ----
3047 if (FormatStr.contains('%')) 0
3048 return nullptr; // we found a format specifier, bail out. 0
3049 ----
3050 // sprintf(str, fmt) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 str, align 1 fmt, strlen(fmt)+1) ----
3051 B.CreateMemCpy( 0
3052 Dest, Align(1), CI->getArgOperand(1), Align(1), ----
3053 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), 0
3054 FormatStr.size() + 1)); // Copy the null byte. 0
3055 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), FormatStr.size()); 0
3056 } ----
3057 ----
3058 // The remaining optimizations require the format string to be "%s" or "%c" ----
3059 // and have an extra operand. ----
3060 if (FormatStr.size() != 2 || FormatStr[0] != '%' || CI->arg_size() < 3) 0
3061 return nullptr; 0
3062 ----
3063 // Decode the second character of the format string. ----
3064 if (FormatStr[1] == 'c') { 0
3065 // sprintf(dst, "%c", chr) --> *(i8*)dst = chr; *((i8*)dst+1) = 0 ----
3066 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isIntegerTy()) 0
3067 return nullptr; 0
3068 Value *V = B.CreateTrunc(CI->getArgOperand(2), B.getInt8Ty(), "char"); 0
3069 Value *Ptr = castToCStr(Dest, B); 0
3070 B.CreateStore(V, Ptr); 0
3071 Ptr = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Ptr, B.getInt32(1), "nul"); 0
3072 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), Ptr); 0
3073 ----
3074 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1); 0
3075 } ----
3076 ----
3077 if (FormatStr[1] == 's') { 0
3078 // sprintf(dest, "%s", str) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 dest, align 1 str, ----
3079 // strlen(str)+1) ----
3080 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isPointerTy()) 0
3081 return nullptr; 0
3082 ----
3083 if (CI->use_empty()) 0
3084 // sprintf(dest, "%s", str) -> strcpy(dest, str) ----
3085 return copyFlags(*CI, emitStrCpy(Dest, CI->getArgOperand(2), B, TLI)); 0
3086 ----
3087 uint64_t SrcLen = GetStringLength(CI->getArgOperand(2)); 0
3088 if (SrcLen) { 0
3089 B.CreateMemCpy( 0
3090 Dest, Align(1), CI->getArgOperand(2), Align(1), ----
3091 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), SrcLen)); 0
3092 // Returns total number of characters written without null-character. ----
3093 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), SrcLen - 1); 0
3094 } else if (Value *V = emitStpCpy(Dest, CI->getArgOperand(2), B, TLI)) { 0
3095 // sprintf(dest, "%s", str) -> stpcpy(dest, str) - dest ----
3096 // Handle mismatched pointer types (goes away with typeless pointers?). ----
3097 V = B.CreatePointerCast(V, B.getInt8PtrTy()); 0
3098 Dest = B.CreatePointerCast(Dest, B.getInt8PtrTy()); 0
3099 Value *PtrDiff = B.CreatePtrDiff(B.getInt8Ty(), V, Dest); 0
3100 return B.CreateIntCast(PtrDiff, CI->getType(), false); 0
3101 } ----
3102 ----
3103 bool OptForSize = CI->getFunction()->hasOptSize() || 0
3104 llvm::shouldOptimizeForSize(CI->getParent(), PSI, BFI, 0
3105 PGSOQueryType::IRPass); 0
3106 if (OptForSize) 0
3107 return nullptr; 0
3108 ----
3109 Value *Len = emitStrLen(CI->getArgOperand(2), B, DL, TLI); 0
3110 if (!Len) 0
3111 return nullptr; 0
3112 Value *IncLen = ----
3113 B.CreateAdd(Len, ConstantInt::get(Len->getType(), 1), "leninc"); 0
3114 B.CreateMemCpy(Dest, Align(1), CI->getArgOperand(2), Align(1), IncLen); 0
3115 ----
3116 // The sprintf result is the unincremented number of bytes in the string. ----
3117 return B.CreateIntCast(Len, CI->getType(), false); 0
3118 } ----
3119 return nullptr; 0
3120 } ----
3121 ----
3122 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSPrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
3123 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
3124 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
3125 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType(); 0
3126 if (Value *V = optimizeSPrintFString(CI, B)) { 0
3127 return V; 0
3128 } ----
3129 ----
3130 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, {0, 1}); 0
3131 ----
3132 // sprintf(str, format, ...) -> siprintf(str, format, ...) if no floating ----
3133 // point arguments. ----
3134 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_siprintf) && 0
3135 !callHasFloatingPointArgument(CI)) { 0
3136 FunctionCallee SIPrintFFn = getOrInsertLibFunc(M, *TLI, LibFunc_siprintf, 0
3137 FT, Callee->getAttributes()); ----
3138 CallInst *New = cast(CI->clone()); 0
3139 New->setCalledFunction(SIPrintFFn); 0
3140 B.Insert(New); 0
3141 return New; 0
3142 } ----
3143 ----
3144 // sprintf(str, format, ...) -> __small_sprintf(str, format, ...) if no 128-bit ----
3145 // floating point arguments. ----
3146 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_small_sprintf) && 0
3147 !callHasFP128Argument(CI)) { 0
3148 auto SmallSPrintFFn = getOrInsertLibFunc(M, *TLI, LibFunc_small_sprintf, FT, 0
3149 Callee->getAttributes()); ----
3150 CallInst *New = cast(CI->clone()); 0
3151 New->setCalledFunction(SmallSPrintFFn); 0
3152 B.Insert(New); 0
3153 return New; 0
3154 } ----
3155 ----
3156 return nullptr; 0
3157 } ----
3158 ----
3159 // Transform an snprintf call CI with the bound N to format the string Str ----
3160 // either to a call to memcpy, or to single character a store, or to nothing, ----
3161 // and fold the result to a constant. A nonnull StrArg refers to the string ----
3162 // argument being formatted. Otherwise the call is one with N < 2 and ----
3163 // the "%c" directive to format a single character. ----
3164 Value *LibCallSimplifier::emitSnPrintfMemCpy(CallInst *CI, Value *StrArg, 0
3165 StringRef Str, uint64_t N, ----
3166 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
3167 assert(StrArg || (N < 2 && Str.size() == 1)); 0
3168 ----
3169 unsigned IntBits = TLI->getIntSize(); 0
3170 uint64_t IntMax = maxIntN(IntBits); 0
3171 if (Str.size() > IntMax) 0
3172 // Bail if the string is longer than INT_MAX. POSIX requires ----
3173 // implementations to set errno to EOVERFLOW in this case, in ----
3174 // addition to when N is larger than that (checked by the caller). ----
3175 return nullptr; 0
3176 ----
3177 Value *StrLen = ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Str.size()); 0
3178 if (N == 0) 0
3179 return StrLen; 0
3180 ----
3181 // Set to the number of bytes to copy fron StrArg which is also ----
3182 // the offset of the terinating nul. ----
3183 uint64_t NCopy; ----
3184 if (N > Str.size()) 0
3185 // Copy the full string, including the terminating nul (which must ----
3186 // be present regardless of the bound). ----
3187 NCopy = Str.size() + 1; 0
3188 else ----
3189 NCopy = N - 1; 0
3190 ----
3191 Value *DstArg = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
3192 if (NCopy && StrArg) 0
3193 // Transform the call to lvm.memcpy(dst, fmt, N). ----
3194 copyFlags( 0
3195 *CI, ----
3196 B.CreateMemCpy( 0
3197 DstArg, Align(1), StrArg, Align(1), ----
3198 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), NCopy))); 0
3199 ----
3200 if (N > Str.size()) 0
3201 // Return early when the whole format string, including the final nul, ----
3202 // has been copied. ----
3203 return StrLen; 0
3204 ----
3205 // Otherwise, when truncating the string append a terminating nul. ----
3206 Type *Int8Ty = B.getInt8Ty(); 0
3207 Value *NulOff = B.getIntN(IntBits, NCopy); 0
3208 Value *DstEnd = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(Int8Ty, DstArg, NulOff, "endptr"); 0
3209 B.CreateStore(ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, 0), DstEnd); 0
3210 return StrLen; 0
3211 } ----
3212 ----
3213 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSnPrintFString(CallInst *CI, 0
3214 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
3215 // Check for size ----
3216 ConstantInt *Size = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(1)); 0
3217 if (!Size) 0
3218 return nullptr; 0
3219 ----
3220 uint64_t N = Size->getZExtValue(); 0
3221 uint64_t IntMax = maxIntN(TLI->getIntSize()); 0
3222 if (N > IntMax) 0
3223 // Bail if the bound exceeds INT_MAX. POSIX requires implementations ----
3224 // to set errno to EOVERFLOW in this case. ----
3225 return nullptr; 0
3226 ----
3227 Value *DstArg = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
3228 Value *FmtArg = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
3229 ----
3230 // Check for a fixed format string. ----
3231 StringRef FormatStr; 0
3232 if (!getConstantStringInfo(FmtArg, FormatStr)) 0
3233 return nullptr; 0
3234 ----
3235 // If we just have a format string (nothing else crazy) transform it. ----
3236 if (CI->arg_size() == 3) { 0
3237 if (FormatStr.contains('%')) 0
3238 // Bail if the format string contains a directive and there are ----
3239 // no arguments. We could handle "%%" in the future. ----
3240 return nullptr; 0
3241 ----
3242 return emitSnPrintfMemCpy(CI, FmtArg, FormatStr, N, B); 0
3243 } ----
3244 ----
3245 // The remaining optimizations require the format string to be "%s" or "%c" ----
3246 // and have an extra operand. ----
3247 if (FormatStr.size() != 2 || FormatStr[0] != '%' || CI->arg_size() != 4) 0
3248 return nullptr; 0
3249 ----
3250 // Decode the second character of the format string. ----
3251 if (FormatStr[1] == 'c') { 0
3252 if (N <= 1) { 0
3253 // Use an arbitary string of length 1 to transform the call into ----
3254 // either a nul store (N == 1) or a no-op (N == 0) and fold it ----
3255 // to one. ----
3256 StringRef CharStr("*"); 0
3257 return emitSnPrintfMemCpy(CI, nullptr, CharStr, N, B); 0
3258 } ----
3259 ----
3260 // snprintf(dst, size, "%c", chr) --> *(i8*)dst = chr; *((i8*)dst+1) = 0 ----
3261 if (!CI->getArgOperand(3)->getType()->isIntegerTy()) 0
3262 return nullptr; 0
3263 Value *V = B.CreateTrunc(CI->getArgOperand(3), B.getInt8Ty(), "char"); 0
3264 Value *Ptr = castToCStr(DstArg, B); 0
3265 B.CreateStore(V, Ptr); 0
3266 Ptr = B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Ptr, B.getInt32(1), "nul"); 0
3267 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), Ptr); 0
3268 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1); 0
3269 } ----
3270 ----
3271 if (FormatStr[1] != 's') 0
3272 return nullptr; 0
3273 ----
3274 Value *StrArg = CI->getArgOperand(3); 0
3275 // snprintf(dest, size, "%s", str) to llvm.memcpy(dest, str, len+1, 1) ----
3276 StringRef Str; 0
3277 if (!getConstantStringInfo(StrArg, Str)) 0
3278 return nullptr; 0
3279 ----
3280 return emitSnPrintfMemCpy(CI, StrArg, Str, N, B); 0
3281 } ----
3282 ----
3283 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSnPrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
3284 if (Value *V = optimizeSnPrintFString(CI, B)) { 0
3285 return V; 0
3286 } ----
3287 ----
3288 if (isKnownNonZero(CI->getOperand(1), DL)) 0
3289 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
3290 return nullptr; 0
3291 } ----
3292 ----
3293 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPrintFString(CallInst *CI, 0
3294 IRBuilderBase &B) { ----
3295 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 0); 0
3296 ----
3297 // All the optimizations depend on the format string. ----
3298 StringRef FormatStr; 0
3299 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), FormatStr)) 0
3300 return nullptr; 0
3301 ----
3302 // Do not do any of the following transformations if the fprintf return ----
3303 // value is used, in general the fprintf return value is not compatible ----
3304 // with fwrite(), fputc() or fputs(). ----
3305 if (!CI->use_empty()) 0
3306 return nullptr; 0
3307 ----
3308 // fprintf(F, "foo") --> fwrite("foo", 3, 1, F) ----
3309 if (CI->arg_size() == 2) { 0
3310 // Could handle %% -> % if we cared. ----
3311 if (FormatStr.contains('%')) 0
3312 return nullptr; // We found a format specifier. 0
3313 ----
3314 unsigned SizeTBits = TLI->getSizeTSize(*CI->getModule()); 0
3315 Type *SizeTTy = IntegerType::get(CI->getContext(), SizeTBits); 0
3316 return copyFlags( 0
3317 *CI, emitFWrite(CI->getArgOperand(1), ----
3318 ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, FormatStr.size()), 0
3319 CI->getArgOperand(0), B, DL, TLI)); 0
3320 } ----
3321 ----
3322 // The remaining optimizations require the format string to be "%s" or "%c" ----
3323 // and have an extra operand. ----
3324 if (FormatStr.size() != 2 || FormatStr[0] != '%' || CI->arg_size() < 3) 0
3325 return nullptr; 0
3326 ----
3327 // Decode the second character of the format string. ----
3328 if (FormatStr[1] == 'c') { 0
3329 // fprintf(F, "%c", chr) --> fputc((int)chr, F) ----
3330 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isIntegerTy()) 0
3331 return nullptr; 0
3332 Type *IntTy = B.getIntNTy(TLI->getIntSize()); 0
3333 Value *V = B.CreateIntCast(CI->getArgOperand(2), IntTy, /*isSigned*/ true, 0
3334 "chari"); ----
3335 return copyFlags(*CI, emitFPutC(V, CI->getArgOperand(0), B, TLI)); 0
3336 } ----
3337 ----
3338 if (FormatStr[1] == 's') { 0
3339 // fprintf(F, "%s", str) --> fputs(str, F) ----
3340 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isPointerTy()) 0
3341 return nullptr; 0
3342 return copyFlags( 0
3343 *CI, emitFPutS(CI->getArgOperand(2), CI->getArgOperand(0), B, TLI)); 0
3344 } ----
3345 return nullptr; 0
3346 } ----
3347 ----
3348 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
3349 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
3350 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
3351 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType(); 0
3352 if (Value *V = optimizeFPrintFString(CI, B)) { 0
3353 return V; 0
3354 } ----
3355 ----
3356 // fprintf(stream, format, ...) -> fiprintf(stream, format, ...) if no ----
3357 // floating point arguments. ----
3358 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_fiprintf) && 0
3359 !callHasFloatingPointArgument(CI)) { 0
3360 FunctionCallee FIPrintFFn = getOrInsertLibFunc(M, *TLI, LibFunc_fiprintf, 0
3361 FT, Callee->getAttributes()); ----
3362 CallInst *New = cast(CI->clone()); 0
3363 New->setCalledFunction(FIPrintFFn); 0
3364 B.Insert(New); 0
3365 return New; 0
3366 } ----
3367 ----
3368 // fprintf(stream, format, ...) -> __small_fprintf(stream, format, ...) if no ----
3369 // 128-bit floating point arguments. ----
3370 if (isLibFuncEmittable(M, TLI, LibFunc_small_fprintf) && 0
3371 !callHasFP128Argument(CI)) { 0
3372 auto SmallFPrintFFn = ----
3373 getOrInsertLibFunc(M, *TLI, LibFunc_small_fprintf, FT, 0
3374 Callee->getAttributes()); ----
3375 CallInst *New = cast(CI->clone()); 0
3376 New->setCalledFunction(SmallFPrintFFn); 0
3377 B.Insert(New); 0
3378 return New; 0
3379 } ----
3380 ----
3381 return nullptr; 0
3382 } ----
3383 ----
3384 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFWrite(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
3385 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 3); 0
3386 ----
3387 // Get the element size and count. ----
3388 ConstantInt *SizeC = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(1)); 0
3389 ConstantInt *CountC = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(2)); 0
3390 if (SizeC && CountC) { 0
3391 uint64_t Bytes = SizeC->getZExtValue() * CountC->getZExtValue(); 0
3392 ----
3393 // If this is writing zero records, remove the call (it's a noop). ----
3394 if (Bytes == 0) 0
3395 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0); 0
3396 ----
3397 // If this is writing one byte, turn it into fputc. ----
3398 // This optimisation is only valid, if the return value is unused. ----
3399 if (Bytes == 1 && CI->use_empty()) { // fwrite(S,1,1,F) -> fputc(S[0],F) 0
3400 Value *Char = B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), 0
3401 castToCStr(CI->getArgOperand(0), B), "char"); ----
3402 Type *IntTy = B.getIntNTy(TLI->getIntSize()); 0
3403 Value *Cast = B.CreateIntCast(Char, IntTy, /*isSigned*/ true, "chari"); 0
3404 Value *NewCI = emitFPutC(Cast, CI->getArgOperand(3), B, TLI); 0
3405 return NewCI ? ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1) : nullptr; 0
3406 } ----
3407 } ----
3408 ----
3409 return nullptr; 0
3410 } ----
3411 ----
3412 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPuts(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
3413 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 1); 0
3414 ----
3415 // Don't rewrite fputs to fwrite when optimising for size because fwrite ----
3416 // requires more arguments and thus extra MOVs are required. ----
3417 bool OptForSize = CI->getFunction()->hasOptSize() || 0
3418 llvm::shouldOptimizeForSize(CI->getParent(), PSI, BFI, 0
3419 PGSOQueryType::IRPass); 0
3420 if (OptForSize) 0
3421 return nullptr; 0
3422 ----
3423 // We can't optimize if return value is used. ----
3424 if (!CI->use_empty()) 0
3425 return nullptr; 0
3426 ----
3427 // fputs(s,F) --> fwrite(s,strlen(s),1,F) ----
3428 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(CI->getArgOperand(0)); 0
3429 if (!Len) 0
3430 return nullptr; 0
3431 ----
3432 // Known to have no uses (see above). ----
3433 unsigned SizeTBits = TLI->getSizeTSize(*CI->getModule()); 0
3434 Type *SizeTTy = IntegerType::get(CI->getContext(), SizeTBits); 0
3435 return copyFlags( 0
3436 *CI, ----
3437 emitFWrite(CI->getArgOperand(0), ----
3438 ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, Len - 1), 0
3439 CI->getArgOperand(1), B, DL, TLI)); 0
3440 } ----
3441 ----
3442 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePuts(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &B) { 0
3443 annotateNonNullNoUndefBasedOnAccess(CI, 0); 0
3444 if (!CI->use_empty()) 0
3445 return nullptr; 0
3446 ----
3447 // Check for a constant string. ----
3448 // puts("") -> putchar('\n') ----
3449 StringRef Str; 0
3450 if (getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), Str) && Str.empty()) { 0
3451 // putchar takes an argument of the same type as puts returns, i.e., ----
3452 // int, which need not be 32 bits wide. ----
3453 Type *IntTy = CI->getType(); 0
3454 return copyFlags(*CI, emitPutChar(ConstantInt::get(IntTy, '\n'), B, TLI)); 0
3455 } ----
3456 ----
3457 return nullptr; 0
3458 } ----

3461 // bcopy(src, dst, n) -> llvm.memmove(dst, src, n) ----
3462 return copyFlags(*CI, B.CreateMemMove(CI->getArgOperand(1), Align(1), 0
3463 CI->getArgOperand(0), Align(1), ----
3464 CI->getArgOperand(2))); 0
3465 } ----

3676 ----
3677 Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCall(CallInst *CI, IRBuilderBase &Builder) { 0
3678 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
3679 assert(!CI->isMustTailCall() && "These transforms aren't musttail safe."); 0
3680 ----
3681 // TODO: Split out the code below that operates on FP calls so that ----
3682 // we can all non-FP calls with the StrictFP attribute to be ----
3683 // optimized. ----
3684 if (CI->isNoBuiltin()) 0
3685 return nullptr; 0
3686 ----
3687 LibFunc Func; ----
3688 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
3689 bool IsCallingConvC = TargetLibraryInfoImpl::isCallingConvCCompatible(CI); 0
3690 ----
3691 SmallVector OpBundles; 0
3692 CI->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles); 0
3693 ----
3694 IRBuilderBase::OperandBundlesGuard Guard(Builder); 0
3695 Builder.setDefaultOperandBundles(OpBundles); 0
3696 ----
3697 // Command-line parameter overrides instruction attribute. ----
3698 // This can't be moved to optimizeFloatingPointLibCall() because it may be ----
3699 // used by the intrinsic optimizations. ----
3700 if (EnableUnsafeFPShrink.getNumOccurrences() > 0) 0
3701 UnsafeFPShrink = EnableUnsafeFPShrink; 0
3702 else if (isa(CI) && CI->isFast()) 0
3703 UnsafeFPShrink = true; 0
3704 ----
3705 // First, check for intrinsics. ----
3706 if (IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast(CI)) { 0
3707 if (!IsCallingConvC) 0
3708 return nullptr; 0
3709 // The FP intrinsics have corresponding constrained versions so we don't ----
3710 // need to check for the StrictFP attribute here. ----
3711 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) { 0
3712 case Intrinsic::pow: 0
3713 return optimizePow(CI, Builder); 0
3714 case Intrinsic::exp2: 0
3715 return optimizeExp2(CI, Builder); 0
3716 case Intrinsic::log: 0
3717 case Intrinsic::log2: ----
3718 case Intrinsic::log10: ----
3719 return optimizeLog(CI, Builder); 0
3720 case Intrinsic::sqrt: 0
3721 return optimizeSqrt(CI, Builder); 0
3722 case Intrinsic::memset: 0
3723 return optimizeMemSet(CI, Builder); 0
3724 case Intrinsic::memcpy: 0
3725 return optimizeMemCpy(CI, Builder); 0
3726 case Intrinsic::memmove: 0
3727 return optimizeMemMove(CI, Builder); 0
3728 default: 0
3729 return nullptr; 0

3733 // Also try to simplify calls to fortified library functions. ----
3734 if (Value *SimplifiedFortifiedCI = 0

3748 // If we were able to further simplify, remove the now redundant call. ----
3749 substituteInParent(SimplifiedCI, V); 0
3750 return V; 0
3751 } ----
3752 } 0
3753 return SimplifiedFortifiedCI; 0
3754 } ----
3755 ----
3756 // Then check for known library functions. ----

3758 // We never change the calling convention. ----

3760 return nullptr; 0
3761 if (Value *V = optimizeStringMemoryLibCall(CI, Builder)) 0

3764 return V; 0
3765 switch (Func) { 0
3766 case LibFunc_ffs: 0

3769 return optimizeFFS(CI, Builder); 0
3770 case LibFunc_fls: 0
3771 case LibFunc_flsl: ----
3772 case LibFunc_flsll: ----
3773 return optimizeFls(CI, Builder); 0
3774 case LibFunc_abs: 0

3872 ----
3873 bool FortifiedLibCallSimplifier::isFortifiedCallFoldable( 0
3874 CallInst *CI, unsigned ObjSizeOp, std::optional SizeOp, ----
3875 std::optional StrOp, std::optional FlagOp) { ----
3876 // If this function takes a flag argument, the implementation may use it to ----
3877 // perform extra checks. Don't fold into the non-checking variant. ----
3878 if (FlagOp) { 0
3879 ConstantInt *Flag = dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(*FlagOp)); 0
3880 if (!Flag || !Flag->isZero()) 0
3881 return false; 0
3882 } ----
3883 ----
3884 if (SizeOp && CI->getArgOperand(ObjSizeOp) == CI->getArgOperand(*SizeOp)) 0
3885 return true; 0
3886 ----
3887 if (ConstantInt *ObjSizeCI = 0
3888 dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(ObjSizeOp))) { 0
3889 if (ObjSizeCI->isMinusOne()) 0
3890 return true; 0
3891 // If the object size wasn't -1 (unknown), bail out if we were asked to. ----
3892 if (OnlyLowerUnknownSize) 0
3893 return false; 0
3894 if (StrOp) { 0
3895 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(CI->getArgOperand(*StrOp)); 0
3896 // If the length is 0 we don't know how long it is and so we can't ----
3897 // remove the check. ----
3898 if (Len) 0
3899 annotateDereferenceableBytes(CI, *StrOp, Len); 0
3900 else ----
3901 return false; 0
3902 return ObjSizeCI->getZExtValue() >= Len; 0
3903 } ----
3904 ----
3905 if (SizeOp) { 0
3906 if (ConstantInt *SizeCI = 0
3907 dyn_cast(CI->getArgOperand(*SizeOp))) 0
3908 return ObjSizeCI->getZExtValue() >= SizeCI->getZExtValue(); 0
3909 } ----
3910 } ----
3911 return false; 0
3912 } ----

3991 if (Len) 0

3998 Value *LenV = ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, Len); 0
3999 Value *Ret = emitMemCpyChk(Dst, Src, LenV, ObjSize, B, DL, TLI); 0
4000 // If the function was an __stpcpy_chk, and we were able to fold it into ----
4001 // a __memcpy_chk, we still need to return the correct end pointer. ----
4002 if (Ret && Func == LibFunc_stpcpy_chk) 0

4126 Value *FortifiedLibCallSimplifier::optimizeCall(CallInst *CI, 0
4127 IRBuilderBase &Builder) { ----
4128 // FIXME: We shouldn't be changing "nobuiltin" or TLI unavailable calls here. ----
4129 // Some clang users checked for _chk libcall availability using: ----
4130 // __has_builtin(__builtin___memcpy_chk) ----
4131 // When compiling with -fno-builtin, this is always true. ----
4132 // When passing -ffreestanding/-mkernel, which both imply -fno-builtin, we ----
4133 // end up with fortified libcalls, which isn't acceptable in a freestanding ----
4134 // environment which only provides their non-fortified counterparts. ----
4135 // ----
4136 // Until we change clang and/or teach external users to check for availability ----
4137 // differently, disregard the "nobuiltin" attribute and TLI::has. ----
4138 // ----
4139 // PR23093. ----
4140 ----
4141 LibFunc Func; ----
4142 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
4143 bool IsCallingConvC = TargetLibraryInfoImpl::isCallingConvCCompatible(CI); 0
4144 ----
4145 SmallVector OpBundles; 0
4146 CI->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles); 0
4147 ----
4148 IRBuilderBase::OperandBundlesGuard Guard(Builder); 0
4149 Builder.setDefaultOperandBundles(OpBundles); 0
4150 ----
4151 // First, check that this is a known library functions and that the prototype ----
4152 // is correct. ----
4153 if (!TLI->getLibFunc(*Callee, Func)) 0
4154 return nullptr; 0
4155 ----
4156 // We never change the calling convention. ----
4157 if (!ignoreCallingConv(Func) && !IsCallingConvC) 0
4158 return nullptr; 0
4159 ----
4160 switch (Func) { 0
4161 case LibFunc_memcpy_chk: 0
4162 return optimizeMemCpyChk(CI, Builder); 0
4163 case LibFunc_mempcpy_chk: 0
4164 return optimizeMemPCpyChk(CI, Builder); 0
4165 case LibFunc_memmove_chk: 0
4166 return optimizeMemMoveChk(CI, Builder); 0
4167 case LibFunc_memset_chk: 0
4168 return optimizeMemSetChk(CI, Builder); 0
4169 case LibFunc_stpcpy_chk: 0
4170 case LibFunc_strcpy_chk: ----
4171 return optimizeStrpCpyChk(CI, Builder, Func); 0
4172 case LibFunc_strlen_chk: 0
4173 return optimizeStrLenChk(CI, Builder); 0
4174 case LibFunc_stpncpy_chk: 0
4175 case LibFunc_strncpy_chk: ----
4176 return optimizeStrpNCpyChk(CI, Builder, Func); 0
4177 case LibFunc_memccpy_chk: 0
4178 return optimizeMemCCpyChk(CI, Builder); 0
4179 case LibFunc_snprintf_chk: 0
4180 return optimizeSNPrintfChk(CI, Builder); 0
4181 case LibFunc_sprintf_chk: 0
4182 return optimizeSPrintfChk(CI, Builder); 0
4183 case LibFunc_strcat_chk: 0
4184 return optimizeStrCatChk(CI, Builder); 0
4185 case LibFunc_strlcat_chk: 0
4186 return optimizeStrLCat(CI, Builder); 0
4187 case LibFunc_strncat_chk: 0
4188 return optimizeStrNCatChk(CI, Builder); 0
4189 case LibFunc_strlcpy_chk: 0
4190 return optimizeStrLCpyChk(CI, Builder); 0
4191 case LibFunc_vsnprintf_chk: 0
4192 return optimizeVSNPrintfChk(CI, Builder); 0
4193 case LibFunc_vsprintf_chk: 0
4194 return optimizeVSPrintfChk(CI, Builder); 0
4195 default: 0
4196 break; 0
4197 } ----
4198 return nullptr; 0
4199 } 0
